)@@G@@CDNCTDDC, )4@^@@@@E[ME))C1DC(GC-[E-[ 0?AC)@#@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@[[.     MR
)@@G@@THIS ROUTINE HAS THREE ENTRY POINTS @[@@[[.     @F@@[[.     EBO$X  - CONMS
)@@G@@VERT THE BINARY NR IN A0 TO OCTAL FIELDDATA     @[@@[[.     @F@@[[.     MT
)@@G@@EBD$X - CONVERT THE BINARY NR IN A0 TO DECIMAL FIELDDATA    @[@@[[.     MU
)@@G@@@E@@[[.     CONVERT - CONVERT THE FIELDDATA NR IN X2 TO BINARY    @[@@[[MV
)@@G@@.     @F@@[[.     FOR EBO$X AND EBD$X, 0,X11 CONTAINS (S1, S3, H2) THE NMW
)@@G@@R OF  @F@@[[.     CHARACTERS IN THE OUTPUT AREA, THE NR OF DIGITS TO GETMX
)@@G@@,     @D@@[[.     AND THE ADDRESS OF WHERE TO PUT THE CONVERTED NR@[@@[[MY
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@          AXR$      .   @]@@@@$(1)  .     @B@[@@EBO$X*    LMMZ
)@@G@@J       A1,ET           .     @I@@[[EBO$X*    LMJ       A1,ET           NA
)@@G@@. CONVERT BINARY NR IN A0 TO OCTAL FIELDDATA    @B[@@@          DSL     NB
)@@G@@  A0,36           .     @B@@@@EL        DSC       A0,3            .     NC
)@@G@@@B@@@@          SSL       A0,33           .     @B@[@@          A,14    ND
)@@G@@  A0,060          .     @B@@[[          A,U       A0,060          .     NE
)@@G@@@B@[@@          EX        ES,*A3          .     @G@@[[          EX      NF
)@@G@@  INSRTC,*A3       . INSERT CHARACTER IN OUTPUT WORD  @B]@@@          JGNG
)@@G@@D       A4,EL           .     @B@[@@          J         1,11            NH
)@@G@@.     @B@@[[          J         1,X11            .    @B@[@@EBD$X*    LMNI
)@@G@@J       A1,ET           .     @H@@[[EBD$X*    LMJ       A1,ET           NJ
)@@G@@. BINARY NUMBER IN A0 TO DECIMAL FIELDDATA@B@[@@          S         A0,RNK
)@@G@@1           .     @E@@[[          S         A0,R1           . NUMBER TO NL
)@@G@@BE CONVERTED@B#@@@          LM        A1,R1           .     @B@[@@EM    NM
)@@G@@    L,14      A0,0            .     @B@[@@          DI,14     A0,10     NN
)@@G@@      .     @B@[@@          A,14      A1,060          .     @B@[@@      NO
)@@G@@    DSC       A0,36           .     @B@[@@          EX        ES,*A3    NP
)@@G@@      .     @B@[@@          AN,14     A4,1            .     @E@@[[EM    NQ
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,0             . ZERO FOR DIVISION    @E@@[[          DINR
)@@G@@,U      A0,10            . LOP OFF BOTTOM DIGIT @F@@[[          A,U     NS
)@@G@@  A1,060           . MAKE REMAINDER FIELDDATA   @I@@[[          DSC     NT
)@@G@@  A0,36            . REVERSE REMAINDER + QUOTIENT FOR NXT DIV     @F@@[[NU
)@@G@@          EX        INSRTC,*A3       . INSERT CHARACTER IN OUTPUT @B@@[[NV
)@@G@@          AN,U      A4,1             .    @BA@@@          TN        A4  NW
)@@G@@            .     @B@[@@          JNZ       A1,EM           .     @G@@[[NX
)@@G@@          JNZ       A1,EM           . ALL OF BINARY NUMBER CONVERTED?   NY
)@@G@@@B@[@@          L,14      A0,'-'          .     @B@@[[          L,U     NZ
)@@G@@  A0,'-'          .     @B]@@@          L         A1,SPACES       .     OA
)@@G@@@B@@@@          TP        R1              .     @B@[@@          J       OB
)@@G@@  EP              .     @G@@[[          J         EP              . PUT OC
)@@G@@IN MINUS SIGN IF NEGATIVE     @B[@@@          JP        A4,EN           OD
)@@G@@.     @B@[@@          J         1,11            .     @I@@[[          J OE
)@@G@@        1,X11            . ALL CHARACTERS REQUESTED HAVE BEEN FILLED    OF
)@@G@@@B@[@@EN        L         A0,A1           .     @D@@[[EN        L       OG
)@@G@@  A0,A1           . LOAD BLANKS     @B]@@@          SSC       A1,6      OH
)@@G@@      .     @B@[@@EP        EX        ES,*A3          .     @F@@[[EP    OI
)@@G@@    EX        INSRTC,*A3       . FRONT FILL WITH BLANKS     @B[@@@      OJ
)@@G@@    JGD       A4,EN           .     @B@[@@          J         1,11      OK
)@@G@@      .     @C@@[[          J         1,X11            . RETURN   @B[@@@OL
)@@G@@ET        LA        A2,(-1,0)       .     @B@@@@          L         A3,AOM
)@@G@@2           .     @B@[@@          LXM       A2,0,11         .     @B@[@@ON
)@@G@@          LXM,11    A3,0,11         .     @B@[@@          L,13      A4,0OO
)@@G@@,11         .     @F@@[[          LXM       A2,0,X11         . ADDRESS OOP
)@@G@@F OUTPUT WORD     @F@@[[          LXM,S3    A3,0,X11         . NR DIGITSOQ
)@@G@@ IN A0 TO GET     @G@@[[          L,S1      A4,0,X11         . NR CHARACOR
)@@G@@TERS IN OUTPUT AREA     @B#@@@          JGD       A4,0,A1         .     OS
)@@G@@@B@@@@          J         0,A1            .     @B@[@@ES        LMJ     OT
)@@G@@  A3,EF           .     @]@@[[INSRTC .    @F@@[[ES        LMJ       A3,EOU
)@@G@@F            . PUT A CHARACTER IN A WORD  @B@[@@          S,12      A0,0OV
)@@G@@,A2         .     @B@@[[          S,S2      A0,0,A2         .     @B@[@@OW
)@@G@@          S,11      A0,0,A2         .     @B@@[[          S,S3      A0,0OX

)@@G@@3           .     @B@[@@          LXM,14    A3,5            .     @G@@[[PE

)@@G@@@B[@@@          J         0,A0            .     @B@[@@CONVERT*  SZ      PG
)@@G@@  A4               .    @H@@[[CONVERT*  SZ        A4               . CONPH

)@@G@@60           . TO BINARY AND LEAVES IT IN         CPD002    @I@@@@      PK

)@@G@@ . PUT SUM OF DIGITS IN X2 TO RETURN@C[@@@          J         0,X11     QO
)@@G@@       . GO BACK  @]@@@@$(0)  .     @^@@@@SPACES    '      '  .   @B@@@@QP
)@@G@@VALUE     +         0                .    @I@@@@C1        +         0   QQ
)@@G@@             .                                    CPD002    @I@@@@I DO 9QR
)@@G@@ , + I*1                       .                                    CPD0QS
)@@G@@02    @I@@@@C2        +         0                .                      QT

)@@G@@___       AA        A4,C2-060,A1     . ADD 10'S *[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@[$(1)  RG
)@@G@@    AXR$  . @C@@@[  . THIS ROUTINE HANDLES DRUM FILE MANIPULATION @B@@@[RH
)@@G@@  . THE FIRST IS TO MOVE FORWARD IN A FILE@I@@@[PSED*     SZ        A5  RI
)@@G@@             . ZERO TO HOLD ADDRESS AT START OF LAST TRA    @H@@@[      RJ
)@@G@@    J         PSFDA+1          . GO GET THE ADDRESS OF HIGHEST TRACK    RK
)@@G@@@G@@@[PSFD*     SX        X2,A5            . X2 HAS COUNT OF HOW FAR TO RL
)@@G@@MOVE  @F@@@[          TNE       A5,(037777777777) . IS IT A PHONEY COUNTRM
)@@G@@?     @F@@@[          J         PSFDA            . YES, MOVE TO END OF FRN
)@@G@@ILE   @H@@@[          LA        A0,DRPKT+5       . NO, MOVE FORWARD USERRO
)@@G@@ NO. OF SECTORS   @I@@@[          AA        A0,A5            . LOAD CURRRP
)@@G@@ENT ADDRESS AND ADD COUNT TO IT     @E@@@[          SA        A0,DRPKT+5RQ
)@@G@@       . STORE BACK IN PACKET @B@@@[          J         UPBLCK          RR
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@[PSFDA     LA,U      A5,64            . COUNT TO GET TO END ORS
)@@G@@F LAST TRACK@E@@@[          DL        A0,FILEN         . LOAD CURRENT FIRT
)@@G@@LENAME@F@@@[          DS        A0,FITEM         . STORE IT IN FACIT$ PARU
)@@G@@CKET  @F@@@[          DS        A0,FILNM         . STORE IT IN MSG PACKERV
)@@G@@T     @E@@@[          LA,U      A0,FITEM         . LOAD FACIT$ PACKET   RW
)@@G@@@H@@@[          ER        FACIT$           . GET THE ADDRESS OF THE HIGHRX
)@@G@@EST TRACK   @G@@@[          LA        A6,DRPKT+5       . LOAD CURRENT ADRY
)@@G@@DRESS WE ARE AT   @H@@@[          LA,H1     A0,FITEM+9       . LOAD THE RZ
)@@G@@HIGH TRACK (IN NO. OF TRACKS) @F@@@[          LSSL      A0,6            SA
)@@G@@ . SHIFT FOR SECTOR COUNT     @H@@@[          AA        A0,A5           SB
)@@G@@ . ADD INCREMENT (0 FOR PSE, 64 FOR PSF)  @F@@@[          SA        A0,DSC
)@@G@@RPKT+5       . STORE NEW ADDRESS IN PACKET@F@@@[          LA,H1     A0,FSD
)@@G@@ITEM+9       . RELOAD HIGHEST TRACK NUMBER@H@@@[          E$BD      6,TRSE
)@@G@@K$,6         . CONVERT OCTAL TRACKS TO FIELD-DATA     @C@@@[          LASF
)@@G@@,H1     A0,FITEM+9       . RELOAD   @F@@@[          LSSL      A0,6      SG
)@@G@@       . SHIFT FOR SECTOR VALUE     @H@@@[          E$BD      6,SEC$,6  SH
)@@G@@       . CONVERT OCTAL SECTORS TO FIELD-DATA    @D@@@[          LA      SI
)@@G@@  A0,MSG           . LOAD FIRST MSG @F@@@[          ER        PRINT$    SJ
)@@G@@       . HIGHEST TRACK REFERENCED IS@D@@@[          LA        A0,MSGA   SK
)@@G@@       . LOAD SECOND MSG@E@@@[          ER        PRINT$           . BEGSL
)@@G@@INS AT SECTOR     @H@@@[UPBLCK    SLJ       QGETAD            . GET ADDRSM
)@@G@@ OF FILE INFO TABLE IN A0     @H@@@[          LA        A1,DRPKT+5      SN
)@@G@@  . NEW CURRENT DRUM POSITION IN SECTORS  @G@@@[          S         A1,2SO
)@@G@@,A0           . CURRENT BLOCK (SECTOR) COUNT    @F@@@[          J       SP
)@@G@@  CDIMGE            . READ NEXT CPD COMMAND     @D@@@[/ . THIS HANDLES MSQ
)@@G@@OVING BACKWARD OR REWINDING THE FILE@H@@@[PSBD*     SX        X2,A1     SR
)@@G@@       . X2 HAS SECTOR COUNT  FOR MOVE BACK     @F@@@[          LNA     SS
)@@G@@  A0,A1            . MAKE IT A NEGATIVE NUMBER  @G@@@[          AA      ST
)@@G@@  A0,DRPKT+5       . ADD THE CURRENT ADDRESS TO IT    @I@@@[          JNSU
)@@G@@        A0,NEG           . NEG-WE ARE BACK BEFORE START ZERO IT OUT     SV
)@@G@@@G@@@[          SA        A0,DRPKT+5       . STILL IN FILE STORE NEW ADDSW
)@@G@@RESS  @B@@@[          SLJ       QGETAD            .   @B@@@[          LASX
)@@G@@        A1,DRPKT+5        .   @G@@@[          S         A1,2,A0         SY
)@@G@@  . PUT NEW SECTOR COUNT IN TABLE   @B@@@[          J         CDIMGE    SZ
)@@G@@        .   @I@@@[NEG       SZ        DRPKT+5          . RESET ADDRESS TTA
)@@G@@O ZERO (BEGINNING OF FILE)    @E@@@[          CLRF                      TB
)@@G@@ . CLEAR FILE COUNT     @E@@@[          CLRR                       . CLETC
)@@G@@AR SECTOR COUNT   @E@@@[          J         CDIMGE           . ALL DONE TD
)@@G@@ GET OUT    @H@@@[/ . THIS PORTION IS SET UP TO READ A MASS STORAGE FILETE
)@@G@@ IN SECTOR SIZE BLOCKS. @I@@@[  . THE USER CAN CHANGE THE BLOCK SIZE ANDTF
)@@G@@/OR CONTROL THE NUMBER OF BLOCKS READ.    @D@@@[DREAD*    NOP           TG
)@@G@@             . ENTRY POINT    @G@@@]          SLJ       QGETAD          TH
)@@G@@  . GET LATEST FILE DATA ADDRESS    @E@@@]          LA        A1,2,A0   TI
)@@G@@        . PICK UP DRUM ADDRESS@E@@@]          SA        A1,DRPKT+5      TJ
)@@G@@  . SAVE IN DRUM PACKET @G@#@[          LA        A8,SWITCH        . TESTK
)@@G@@T TO SEE IF WE HAVE ENTERED   @G@@@#          LA,H1     A8,3,A0         TL
)@@G@@  . TEST TO SEE IF WE HAVE ENTERED  @G@ @#          SA        A8,MAXREC TM
)@@G@@        . SAVE IN MAXIMUM RECORD TO READ  @G@@@           SA        A8,MTN
)@@G@@AXSEC         . SAVE IN MAXIMUM RECORD TO READ  @H@@@[          JNZ     TO
)@@G@@  A8,DREADA+1      . BEFORE (PARAMETERS ARE ALREADY SET)    @D@#@[      TP
)@@G@@    LA,U      A8,1             . NO, WE HAVEN'T @D@#@[          SA      TQ
)@@G@@  A8,SWITCH        . SET THE SWITCH @E@@@#          LA        A8,A0     TR
)@@G@@        . SAVE A0 FOR LATER   @B@@@[          DL        A0,FILEN        TS
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@[          DS        A0,FITEM         .    @B@@@[          LATT
)@@G@@,U      A0,FITEM         .    @G@@@[          ER        FACIT$          TU
)@@G@@ . GET HIGHEST TRACK REFERENCED     @B@@@[          L,H1      A0,FITEM+9TV
)@@G@@       .    @B@@@[          A,U       A0,1             .    @E@@@[      TW
)@@G@@    LSSL      A0,6             . CONVERT TO SECTORS   @B@@@^          SATX
)@@G@@        A8,MAXSEC         .   @B@@@^          LA        A8,A0           TY
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@^          LA        A0,MAXSEC         .   @C@@@^          SATZ
)@@G@@,H1     A8,3,A0                  .  @H@^@[          S         A0,MAXSEC UA
)@@G@@       . SECTORS TO READ MUST BE LESS THAN THIS @H@@@^          S       UB
)@@G@@  A8,MAXSEC        . SECTORS TO READ MUST BE LESS THAN THIS @E@^@#      UC
)@@G@@    SA,H1     A0,3,A8           . ALSO SAVE IT IN QTAB@G@@@[          SZUD
)@@G@@        FIVE             .  ADDRESS OF A NON ALLOCATED TRACK@F@@@[      UE
)@@G@@    SZ        NRFIVE           . NR OF NONWRITTEN TRACKS    @H@@@[      UF
)@@G@@    GETFLD    SAMECD           . SEE IF THE BLOCK SIZE IS TO BE CHANGED UG
)@@G@@@G@@@[          JZ        A2,DREADA        . NO, GO READ IN SECTOR SIZE UH
)@@G@@BLOCKS@F@@@[          SA        A1,X2            . STORE THE MULTIPLE INUI
)@@G@@ X2   @E@@@[          LMJ       X11,CONVERT      . CONVERT TO BINARY    UJ
)@@G@@@H@@@[          SX        X2,A5            . GET READY TO MODIFY THE BLOUK
)@@G@@CK SIZE     @G@@@[          SX        X2,A9            . A9 USED TO INCRUL
)@@G@@EMENT ADDRESS     @G@@@[          MSI,U     A5,28            . CONVERT IUM
)@@G@@T TO NUMBER OF WORDS    @E@@@[          SA,H1     A5,DRPKT+4       . STOUN
)@@G@@RE IN DRUM PACKET @F@@@[          J         $+2              . JUMP AROUUO
)@@G@@ND A9 MODIFICATION@H@@@[DREADA    LA,U      A9,1             . BLOCK SIZUP
)@@G@@E NOT MODIFIED INCREMENT BY 1 @E@@@[          DL        A0,FILEN        UQ
)@@G@@ . GET THE FILENAME     @D@@@[          DS        A0,DRPKT         . STOUR
)@@G@@RE IN PACKET@D@@@[          L         A0,DRPKT+5       . ADDRESS TO READUS
)@@G@@@E@@@[          TG        A0,MAXSEC        . IS AREA IN FILE RANGE@F@@@[UT
)@@G@@          J         FINISH           . ADDRESS OUTSIDE FILE LIMITS@E@@@[UU
)@@G@@          LA,U      A0,DRPKT         . LOAD DRUM PACKET     @D@@@[      UV
)@@G@@    ER        IOW$             . READ THE FILE  @E@@@[          LA,S1   UW
)@@G@@  A0,DRPKT+3       . LOAD STATUS CODE     @I@@@[          TNE,U     A0,5UX
)@@G@@             . 05--ATTEMPT TO READ FROM AREA NOT WRITTEN    @F@@@[      UY
)@@G@@    J         NOWRIT           . HAVE NOT WRITTEN INTO TRACK@B@@@[      UZ
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A0,022           .    @B@@@[          J         FINISH    VA
)@@G@@       .    @I@@@[          L         A0,NRFIVE        . ARE THERE ANY NVB
)@@G@@ON WRIT TRKS SINCE LAST RD    @ @@@[          JZ        A0,DREADB @H@@@[VC
)@@G@@          L         A0,FIVE          . ADDRESS OF LAST SECTOR STARTING 0VD
)@@G@@5S    @ @@@[          E$BD      6,OLD05,6 @F@@@[          L         A0,DVE
)@@G@@RPKT+5       . SECTOR IN NEW WRITTEN AREA @ @@@[          E$BD      6,NOVF
)@@G@@N05,6 @B@@@[          DL        A0,FILEN         .    @B@@@[          DSVG
)@@G@@        A0,NONEW5        .    @C@@@[          L         A0,(P  2,19,NONEVH
)@@G@@W5)     .   @B@@@[          ER        PRINT$           .    @D@@@[      VI
)@@G@@    SZ        FIVE             . CLEAR ADDRESS  @B@@@[          SZ      VJ
)@@G@@  NRFIVE           .    @]@@@[DREADB  .   @H@@@[          LA,H2     A0,DVK
)@@G@@RPKT+3       . VALID READ:  LOAD NO. OF WORDS READ    @C@@@[          SAVL
)@@G@@,H2     A0,NOWDS$        . SAVE IT  @]@@@[BUMPAD  .   @D@@@]          SLVM
)@@G@@J       QGETAD            . GET FILE DATA @J@@@]          LA        A1,2VN
)@@G@@,A0           . DRPKT+5                         . GET OLD VALUE   @D@@@]VO

)@@G@@  A0,A9            . BUMP IT  @E@@@[          SA        A0,DRPKT+5      VR
)@@G@@ . STORE NEW ADDRESS    @C@@@[          J         *DREAD           . JUMVS
)@@G@@P BACK@E@@@[NOWRIT                               . AREA HAS 05 RETURN   VT
)@@G@@@B@@@[          TZ        NRFIVE           .    @G@@@[          J       VU
)@@G@@  STORWD           . HAVE WRITTEN MESSAGE ALREADY     @B@@@[          DLVV
)@@G@@        A0,FILEN         .    @B@@@[          DS        A0,NEW05        VW
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@[          LA        A0,DRPKT+5       .    @G@@@[          S VX
)@@G@@        A0,FIVE          . ADDRESS OF SECTOR CAUSING 05     @B@@@[      VY
)@@G@@    E$BD      6,NWSC05,6       .    @B@@@[          L         A0,(P  2,1VZ
)@@G@@3,NEW05)    @F@@@[          ER        PRINT$           .  AREA NOT WRITTWA
)@@G@@EN INTO     @D@@@[STORWD    SZ        NOWDS$           . NR WORDS READ  WB
)@@G@@@ @@@[          L         A0,NRFIVE @^@@@[          A,U       A0,1@ @@@[WC
)@@G@@          S         A0,NRFIVE @B@@@[          J         BUMPAD          WD
)@@G@@ .    @G@@@[FINISH    SZ        SWITCH           . EOF ENCOUNTERED  ZEROWE
)@@G@@ OUT SWITCH @B@@@[          SZ        FIVE             .    @B@@@[      WF
)@@G@@    SZ        NRFIVE           .    @I@@@[          LA,U      A0,28     WG
)@@G@@       . RESET BLOCK SIZE TO 1 SECTOR JUST IN CASE    @D@@@[          SAWH
)@@G@@,H1     A0,DRPKT+4       . STORE IN PACKET@E@@@[          INCR          WI
)@@G@@             . UP THE BLOCK COUNT   @E@@@[          SLJ       PRTEFX    WJ
)@@G@@       . EOF ENCOUNTERED AT   @E@@@[          SZ        DUPPNT          WK
)@@G@@ . ZERO DRUM TAPE FLAG  @B@@@[          J         CDIMGE           .    WL
)@@G@@@F@@@[/ . ROUTINE TO WRITE TO A MASS STORAGE FILE.  DATA COMES FROM TAPEWM
)@@G@@@E@@@[DWRTE*    DL        A0,F2NAM         . LOAD THE FILENAME    @D@@@[WN
)@@G@@          DS        A0,DRPKT         . STORE IN PACKET@G@@@[          LAWO
)@@G@@,H2     A0,NOWDS$        . NUMBER OF WORDS IN THE THE BLOCK @H@@@[      WP
)@@G@@    SA        A0,A2            . USE A2 TO POINT TO LAST VALID WORD     WQ
)@@G@@@H@@@[          LXI,U     A2,1             . INCREMENT VALUE FOR ZERO FIWR
)@@G@@LLING WORD  @G@@@[          SA,H1     A0,DRPKT+4       . STORE NUMBER OFWS
)@@G@@ WORDS IN PACKET  @E@@@[          LA,U      A6,010           . STORE WRIWT
)@@G@@TE FUNCTION @B@@@[          SA,S2     A6,DRPKT+3       .    @E@@@[      WU
)@@G@@    DSL       A0,36            . SHIFT FOR DIVISION   @H@@@[          DIWV
)@@G@@,U      A0,28            . DIVIDE TO OBTAIN NUMBER OF SECTORS     @D@@@[WW
)@@G@@          JZ        A1,WRITE         . EVEN MULTIPLE? @H@@@[          AAWX
)@@G@@,U      A0,1             . NO  ADD 1 TO THE NUMBER OF SECTORS     @E@@@[WY
)@@G@@          LA,U      A3,27            . DETERMINE NUMBER     @E@@@[      WZ
)@@G@@    ANA       A3,A1            . OF WORDS TO ZERO FILL@C@@@[BLNKFL    SZXA
)@@G@@        BLOCK,*A2        . ZERO FILL@D@@@[          JGD       A3,BLNKFL XB
)@@G@@       . LAST SECTOR    @F@@@[          SA,H1     A2,DRPKT+4       . STOXC
)@@G@@RE WORD COUNT IN PACKET @G@@@[WRITE     SA        A0,INCREMENT     . STOXD
)@@G@@RE WORD COUNT FOR ADDRESSING  @D@@@[          LA,U      A0,DRPKT        XE
)@@G@@ . WRITE IT OUT   @B@@@[          ER        IOW$             .    @D@@@[XF
)@@G@@          LA        A0,INCREMENT     . BUMP ADDRESS   @D@@@[          AAXG
)@@G@@        A0,DRPKT+5       . AFTER WRITE    @B@@@[          SA        A0,DXH
)@@G@@RPKT+5       .    @E@@@[          LA,U      A6,020           . RESET PACXI
)@@G@@KET FOR READ@B@@@[          SA,S2     A6,DRPKT+3       .    @C@@@[      XJ
)@@G@@    J         *RITE            .   GET OUT@#@@@[/ . DATA AREA     @]@@@[XK
)@@G@@$(0)  .     @B@@@[P         FORM      12,6,18          .    @B@@@[MSG   XL
)@@G@@    P  2,11,MSGPKT             .    @B@@@[MSGA      P  2,5,MSGPKTA      XM
)@@G@@       .    @B@@@[INCREMENT  +        0                .    @#@@@[FIVE  XN
)@@G@@     + 0    @#@@@[NRFIVE     + 0    @#@@@[MAXSEC     + 0    @B@@@[SWITCHXO
)@@G@@*   +         0                .    @D@@@[DRPKT*    +         0         XP
)@@G@@       . DRUM PACKET    @B@@@[          +         0                .    XQ
)@@G@@@B@@@[          +         0                .    @B@@@[          +       XR

)@@G@@@B@@@[          +         0                .    @F@@@[FITEM     +       XT
)@@G@@  0                . PACKET FOR FACIT$ REQUEST  @B@@@[          +       XU

)@@G@@  0                .    @B@@@[          +         0                .    XZ
)@@G@@@B@@@[          +         0                .    @E@@@[MSGPKT  'THE HIGHEYA
)@@G@@ST TRACK REFERENCED OF FILE      '  .     @^@@@[FILNM  '            '  .YB
)@@G@@@#@@@[     '  IS  '  .  @#@@@[TRK$  '      '  . @A@@@[MSGPKTA  'THIS BEGYC
)@@G@@INS AT SECTOR'    @#@@@[SEC$  '      '  . @H@@@[NEW05      '            YD
)@@G@@ HAS AN AREA WHICH HAS NOT BEEN WRITTEN INTO AT '     @^@@@[           'YE

)@@G@@RACK CONTAINING SECTOR '       .    @#@@@[OLD05     + 0     @B@@@[      YI
)@@G@@    END                        .    ___       SLJ       QGETAD          YJ
)@@G@@  . GET FILE DATA @J@@@]          LA        A1,2,A0           . DRPKT+5 YK
)@@G@@                        *[S@@@*SDFF*@I@@[[.     GENERAL TAPE READ ROUTINYL
)@@G@@E USED BY DUP, CMP, PRT FUNCTIONS            . 3A     @I@@[[.     CALLINYM
)@@G@@G SEQUENCE     LMJ  X11                                        . 3A     YN
)@@G@@@I@@[[.       +  FILE                                                   YO
)@@G@@         . 3A     @I@@[[.       +  NAME                                 YP
)@@G@@                           . 3A     @I@@[[.       +  4096, BUFFER AREA  YQ
)@@G@@                                             . 3A     @I@@[[.       +  EYR
)@@G@@OF OR EOT RETURN ADDRESS                                       . 3A     YS
)@@G@@@I@@[[.     IF BAD IO (NOT 0, 1, 2, OR 4) TAKE EXIT$                    YT
)@@G@@         . 3A     @I@@[[.     RETURNS NR WORDS READ IN H2 OF NOWDS$     YU

)@@G@@             .    ___EAD*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@].     @G@@@]. THIS ROUTINE OBTDO
)@@G@@AINS THE CURRENT DATE AND TIME FROM THE SYSTEM AND    @G@@@]. COMPUTES TDP
)@@G@@HE CURRENT MONTH AND DAY OF THE WEEK.  IT ALSO PRODUCES     @G@@@]. SPECDQ
)@@G@@IAL MESSAGES ON APPROPRIATE DAYS OF THE YEAR.  NOW ISN'T THAT     @^@@@]DR
)@@G@@. REALLY GOOD AND NICE? @[@@@].     @B@@@]         AXR$                 DS
)@@G@@       .    @[@@@].     @C@@@]. THIS PROC IS TO SET UP THE SPECIAL MESSADT
)@@G@@GES.  @[@@@].     @]@@@]SP* PROC 1. @ @@@]          +         SP(1,1).  DU
)@@G@@@B@@@]          +         SP(1,2)-1,SP(1,3).    @#@@@]          END.    DV
)@@G@@@B@@@]P        FORM      12,6,18           .    @[@@@]$(1)  @G@@@]SIGTURDW
)@@G@@*  ER        DATE$             . GET DATE AND TIME FROM SYSTEM    @F@@@]DX
)@@G@@         SA        A0,DATE           . STORE DATE IN TEMP LOCATION@F@@@]DY
)@@G@@         SA        A1,TIME           . STORE TIME IN TEMP LOCATION@G@@@]DZ
)@@G@@         ER        TDATE$            . GET BIN DATE FOR MONTH SEARCH    EA
)@@G@@@G@@@]         SA        A0,TDATE          . STORE BIN DATE IN TEMP LOCAEB
)@@G@@TION  @F@@@]         SSL       A0,30             . SHIFT FOR MONTH SEARCEC
)@@G@@H     @D@@@]         SSL       A1,24             . SHIFT FOR HOUR @H@@@]ED
)@@G@@         MSI,U     A0,2              . DOUBLE THE INDEX FOR DOUBLE WRD MEE
)@@G@@ONTHS @E@@@]         DL        A2,MNTH,A0        . LOAD THE PROPER MONTHEF
)@@G@@@E@@@]         DS        A2,MONTH          . STORE MONTH IN PACKET@E@@@]EG
)@@G@@         LA,T2     A0,DATE           . LOAD DAY OF MONTH    @E@@@]      EH
)@@G@@   SA,T1     A0,DAYYR          . STORE DAY IN PACKET  @F@@@]         LA,EI
)@@G@@T3     A0,DATE           . LOAD YEAR (LAST TWO DIGITS)@D@@@]         SA,EJ

)@@G@@@D@@@]         LA,T3     A1,TIME           . LOAD SECONDS   @D@@@]      EP
)@@G@@   SA,T2     A1,MINSEC         . STORE IN PACKET@D@@@]/. THIS PART COMPUEQ
)@@G@@TES THE PROPER DAY OF THE WEEK.     @E@@@]. THIS ALGORITHIM WILL WORK UNER
)@@G@@TIL THE END OF THE YEAR 2069. @G@@@]. IT ACCOUNTS FOR LEAP YEARS AS WELLES
)@@G@@ AS NORMAL ONES AND WILL CHANGE THE @G@@@]. CENTURY FROM 19 TO 20 WHEN TET
)@@G@@HAT AUSPICIOUS EVENT OCCURS.  SOME OF THE @G@@@]. CODE IS A REAL TAFFY PEU
)@@G@@ULL, WHICH IS QUITE A BIT LIKE FUDGING ONLY     @#@@@]. MUCH STICKIER.  EV
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @F@@@]         LA,S1     A0,TDATE          . LOAD THE CURRENEW
)@@G@@T MONTH     @H@@@]         LA        A6,OFFSET-1,A0    . LOAD THE OFFSETEX
)@@G@@.  THE OFFSET IS THE    @H@@@]         AA,S2     A6,TDATE          . SUMEY
)@@G@@ OF THE DAYS IN THE MONTHS PROCEDING@I@@@]                              EZ
)@@G@@       . THE CURRENT ONE AND ADD TODAYS DATE TO IT    @H@@@]         LA,FA
)@@G@@U      A8,72             . LOAD THE 1ST LEAP YR AFTER THIS WRIT   @G@@@]FB
)@@G@@         LA,S3     A9,TDATE          . LOAD THE CURRENT YEAR (MODULO 64)FC
)@@G@@@E@@@]         AA,U      A9,64             . BRING IT UP TO DATE  @[@@@]FD
)@@G@@.     @E@@@]. THIS PART DETERMINES WHETHER WE HAVE A LEAP YEAR OR NOT.  FE
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @E@@@]TEST1    TG        A8,A9             . IS CURRENT YEARFF
)@@G@@ < 72?@F@@@]         J         TEST2             . NO, GO DO THE NEXT TEFG
)@@G@@ST    @E@@@]         AA,U      A8,4              . YES, ADD 4 TO BASE 72FH
)@@G@@@F@@@]         J         TEST1             . GO BACK AND TEST AGAIN     FI
)@@G@@@D@@@]TEST2    TE        A8,A9             . ARE THEY EQUAL?@G@@@]      FJ
)@@G@@   J         TEST3             . NO, NOT A LEAP YEAR, KEEP GOING  @G@@@]FK
)@@G@@         ANA,U     A0,3              . YES, SEE WHAT MONTH WE ARE IN    FL
)@@G@@@G@@@]         JP        A0,$+3            . AFTER MARCH, NEED AN EXTRA FM
)@@G@@DAY   @G@@@]         JZ        A0,$+2            . IT IS MARCH, NEED AN FN
)@@G@@EXTRA DAY   @H@@@]         J         TEST3             . NO, MUST BE JANFO
)@@G@@ OR FEB, NO EXTRA DAY   @E@@@]         AA,U      A6,1              . ADDFP
)@@G@@ THE EXTRA DAY    @H@@@]TEST3    DSA       A6,36             . NOW TAKE FQ
)@@G@@OUT THE WEEKS PRIOR TO THIS   @G@@@]         DI,U      A6,7             FR
)@@G@@ . ONE AND SAVE THE REMAINDER IN A7 @B@@@]. NOW LET'S CHECK WHAT CENTURYFS
)@@G@@ WE'RE IN   @F@@@]         LA,S3     A10,TDATE         . LOAD THE YEAR (FT
)@@G@@MODULO 64)  @D@@@]         ANA,U     A10,6             . BIAS IT BY 70  FU
)@@G@@@C@@@]         JP        A10,$+5           . < 70?    @C@@@]         JZ FV
)@@G@@       A10,$+4           . = 70?    @D@@@]         AA,U      A10,100    FW

)@@G@@D THE NEW CENTURY @E@@@]         SA,T3     A11,DAYYR         . CHANGE THFY
)@@G@@E PACKET    @[@@@].     @H@@@]. THIS SECTION COMPUTES THE DAY OF THE WEEFZ

)@@G@@         '     AUGUST '              . BE @C@@@]         '  SEPTEMBER ' IQ
)@@G@@             . LOADED   @C@@@]         '    OCTOBER '              . INTIR
)@@G@@O     @B@@@]         '   NOVEMBER '              . THE@C@@@]         '  IS
)@@G@@ DECEMBER '              . PACKET   @F@@@]/.        SPECIAL DATE SECTIONIT
)@@G@@.  CPD CAN PLAY GAMES BY ADDING A   @G@@@].         COMMENT TO SPECIAL DIU
)@@G@@ATES SUCH AS HALLOW5EN 69+1PI93+6663(2    @D@@@].         DAY OR ST. SWIIV
)@@G@@THEN'S DAY, OR WHAT HAVE YOU. @E@@@].         TABLES ARE GENERATED BY PRIW
)@@G@@OC 'SP'. TYPICAL CALL.  @[@@@].     @A@@@].         SP   '1031',2,HALMSGIX
)@@G@@.     @[@@@].     @F@@@].         WHERE 1031 IS HALLOWEEN, OCT. 31, 2 ISIY
)@@G@@ THE COUNT OF THE @G@@@].         WORDS IN THE HALLOWEEN MESSAGE, AND HAIZ
)@@G@@LMSG IS THE LOCATION    @C@@@].         OF THE FIRST WORD OF THE MESSAGEJA
)@@G@@.     @E@@@].         THE COMMENT IS PUT AT THE END OF THE DATE LINE.   JB

)@@G@@   END                         .    ___SP        '0814',E0814-B0814,B081NF
)@@G@@4 .   @C@@@]         SP *[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@U        AXR$  .   @H@@@UB11   NG
)@@G@@    EQU       11               . NEED THIS EXTRA ONE DUE TO OLD CODE    NH
)@@G@@@]@@@U$(1)  .     @^@@@U. OCTAL PRINT ROUTINE   @B@@@UPRTO*     EDIT    NI
)@@G@@  8,14,8,2         .    @[@@@U.     @B@W@U. ALPHA PRINT ROUTINE    WORDSNJ
)@@G@@ SEPERATED  @B@@@W. ALPHA PRINT ROUTINE    WORDS SEPARATED  @B@@@UPRTA* NK
)@@G@@    EDIT      16,8,16,1        .    @[@@@U.     @C@W@U. ALPHA PRINT HARDNL
)@@G@@ TO READ JAMMED TO GETHER     @B@@@W. ALPHA PRINT HARD TO READ JAMMED TONM
)@@G@@GETHER@B@@@UPRTH*     EDIT      16,6,16,1        .    @[@@@U.     @B@@@UNN
)@@G@@. ALPHA PRINT ROUTINE    WORDS SEPERATED  @]@@@UPRTAQ*    . @B@@@U      NO
)@@G@@    SX        X11,PRTAQX11      .   @F@@@U          SLJ       HDR       NP
)@@G@@        . PRINT OUT GENERAL HEADER  @F@@@U          SZ        C$TR      NQ
)@@G@@        . CLEAR OCTAL LINE COUNTER  @G@@@U          LA        A0,NOWDS$ NR
)@@G@@        . GET NUMBER OF WORDS IN BUFFER   @F@@@U          TNZ       A0  NS
)@@G@@              . IF NONE QUIT YOU TURKEY   @E@@@U          J         EXPRNT
)@@G@@TAQ            . RETURN TO SENDER   @D@@@X          LA,U      A1,20     NU
)@@G@@        . LENGTH OF LINE@E@@@X          LMJ       X11,XOPT          . TENV
)@@G@@ST IF X OPTION ON @G@@@U          AN,U      A0,1              . SUBTRACTNW
)@@G@@ ONE FOR THE GREAT JGD  @D@@@U          LR        R2,A0             . OKNX
)@@G@@ HERE WE GO @E@@@U          LX        X10,ONEBLOCK     . SET FOR LOOP INNY
)@@G@@DEXING@A@@@U          SX        X10,SAVEX10     @E@@@UQ$LOOP2    A$EDIT NZ
)@@G@@   AEDITPKT          . ENTER ASCII EDITOR @G@@@U          A$EOCTF    4,COA
)@@G@@$TR            . PRINT IN OCTAL THE LINE NUMBER @B@@@U          LA      OB
)@@G@@  A0,C$TR           .   @D@@@U          A,U       A0,20         . ADD INOC
)@@G@@CREMENT     @F@@@U          SA        A0,C$TR           . SAVE INCREMENTOD
)@@G@@ED COUNTER  @D@@@UQ$LOOP3   LR,U      R3,20-1       . WORDS PER LINE    OE
)@@G@@@E@@@U          A$ESKIP    1                 . SKIP ONE COLUMN    @]@@@UOF
)@@G@@Q$LOOP4   . @B@@@U          LX        X10,SAVEX10       .   @C@@@U      OG
)@@G@@    DL        A1,RANGE          . 037,0176@D@@@U          LA        A0,0OH
)@@G@@,X10         . GET FIRST WORD @B@@@U          SA        A0,W$ORD        OI
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@U          LA,U      A0,0134           . SUBSTITUTE CHARACTEROJ
)@@G@@@F@@@U          TW,Q1     A1,0,X10          . CHECK FIRST CHARACTER     OK
)@@G@@@D@@@U          SA,Q1     A0,W$ORD          . PUT IT BACK   @F@@@U      OL
)@@G@@    TW,Q2     A1,0,X10          . CHECK SECOND CHARACTER    @D@@@U      OM
)@@G@@    SA,Q2     A0,W$ORD          . PUT IT BACK   @E@V@U          TW,Q3   ON
)@@G@@  A0,0,X10          . THIRD CHARACTER     @E@@@V          TW,Q3     A1,0OO
)@@G@@,X10          . THIRD CHARACTER     @D@@@U          SA,Q3     A0,W$ORD  OP
)@@G@@        . PUT IT BACK   @E@V@U          TW,Q4     A0,0,*X10          . FOQ
)@@G@@OURTH CHARACTER   @E@@@V          TW,Q4     A1,0,*X10          . FOURTH OR
)@@G@@CHARACTER   @D@@@U          SA,Q4     A0,W$ORD          . PUT IT BACK   OS
)@@G@@@B@@@U          SX        X10,SAVEX10       .   @F@@@U          A$ECOPY OT
)@@G@@  4,W$ORD           . MOVE IT TO OUTPUT BUFFER  @E@@@U          A$ESKIP OU
)@@G@@  1                 . SKIP ONE COLUMN     @B@@@U          JGD       R3,QOV
)@@G@@E$LOOP2        .  @F@@@UQE$LOOP1   A$EDITX                     . TERMINAOW
)@@G@@TE ASCII EDITOR   @E@@@U          LA        A0,AEPRINT        . (PF 1,30OX
)@@G@@,AEBUF)     @B@@@U          ER        APRINT$           .   @B@@@U      OY
)@@G@@    JGD       R2,Q$LOOP2        .   @E@@@U          J         EXPRTAQ   OZ
)@@G@@         . RETURN TO SENDER   @D@@@UQE$LOOP2  JGD       R2,Q$LOOP4      PA
)@@G@@   . GET NEXT WORD@^@@@U          LR,U      R2,0@ @@@U          J       PB
)@@G@@  QE$LOOP1  @B@@@UEXPRTAQ   LX        X11,PRTAQX11      .   @B@@@U      PC
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             .   @[@@@U.     @C@@@U. ALPHA PRINT HARDPD
)@@G@@ TO READ JAMMED TO GETHER     @]@@@UPRTHQ*    . @B@@@U          SX      PE
)@@G@@  X11,PRTHQX11      .   @F@@@U          SLJ       HDR               . PRPF
)@@G@@INT OUT GENERAL HEADER  @F@@@U          SZ        C$TR              . CLPG
)@@G@@EAR OCTAL LINE COUNTER  @G@@@U          LA        A0,NOWDS$         . GEPH
)@@G@@T NUMBER OF WORDS IN BUFFER   @F@@@U          TNZ       A0              PI
)@@G@@  . IF NONE QUIT YOU TURKEY   @E@@@U          J         EXPRTHQ         PJ
)@@G@@   . RETURN TO SENDER   @B@@@X          LA,U      A1,20             .   PK
)@@G@@@E@@@X          LMJ       X11,XOPT          . TEST IF X OPTION ON @G@@@UPL
)@@G@@          AN,U      A0,1              . SUBTRACT ONE FOR THE GREAT JGD  PM
)@@G@@@D@@@U          LR        R2,A0             . OK HERE WE GO @E@@@U      PN
)@@G@@    LX        X10,ONEBLOCK     . SET FOR LOOP INDEXING@B@@@U          SXPO
)@@G@@        X10,SAVEX10       .   @E@@@UH$LOOP2    A$EDIT    AEDITPKT       PP
)@@G@@   . ENTER ASCII EDITOR @G@@@U          A$EOCTF    4,C$TR            . PPQ
)@@G@@RINT IN OCTAL THE LINE NUMBER @B@@@U          LA        A0,C$TR         PR
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@U          A,U       A0,20         . ADD INCREMENT     @F@@@UPS
)@@G@@          SA        A0,C$TR           . SAVE INCREMENTED COUNTER  @D@@@UPT
)@@G@@H$LOOP3   LR,U      R3,20-1       . WORDS PER LINE    @E@@@U          A$PU
)@@G@@ESKIP    1                 . SKIP ONE COLUMN    @]@@@UH$LOOP4   . @B@@@UPV
)@@G@@          LX        X10,SAVEX10       .   @C@@@U          DL        A1,RPW
)@@G@@ANGE          . 037,0176@D@@@U          LA        A0,0,X10         . GETPX
)@@G@@ FIRST WORD @B@@@U          SA        A0,W$ORD          .   @E@@@U      PY
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,0134           . SUBSTITUTE CHARACTER@F@@@U          TWPZ
)@@G@@,Q1     A1,0,X10          . CHECK FIRST CHARACTER     @D@@@U          SAQA
)@@G@@,Q1     A0,W$ORD          . PUT IT BACK   @F@@@U          TW,Q2     A1,0QB
)@@G@@,X10          . CHECK SECOND CHARACTER    @D@@@U          SA,Q2     A0,WQC
)@@G@@$ORD          . PUT IT BACK   @E@V@U          TW,Q3     A0,0,X10        QD
)@@G@@  . THIRD CHARACTER     @E@@@V          TW,Q3     A1,0,X10          . THQE
)@@G@@IRD CHARACTER     @D@@@U          SA,Q3     A0,W$ORD          . PUT IT BQF
)@@G@@ACK   @E@V@U          TW,Q4     A0,0,*X10          . FOURTH CHARACTER   QG
)@@G@@@E@@@V          TW,Q4     A1,0,*X10          . FOURTH CHARACTER   @D@@@UQH
)@@G@@          SA,Q4     A0,W$ORD          . PUT IT BACK   @B@@@U          SXQI
)@@G@@        X10,SAVEX10       .   @B@@@U          A$ECOPY   4,W$ORD         QJ
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@U          JGD       R3,HE$LOOP2        .  @F@@@UHE$LOOP1   AQK
)@@G@@$EDITX                     . TERMINATE ASCII EDITOR   @E@@@U          LAQL
)@@G@@        A0,AEPRINT        . (PF 1,30,AEBUF)     @B@@@U          ER      QM
)@@G@@  APRINT$           .   @E@@@U          JGD       R2,H$LOOP2        . GOQN
)@@G@@ FOR NEXT LINE    @E@@@U          J         EXPRTHQ            . RETURN QO
)@@G@@TO SENDER   @D@@@UHE$LOOP2  JGD       R2,H$LOOP4         . GET NEXT WORDQP
)@@G@@@^@@@U          LR,U      R2,0@ @@@U          J         HE$LOOP1  @[@@@UQQ
)@@G@@.     @B@@@UEXPRTHQ   LX        X11,PRTHQX11       .  @B@@@U          J QR
)@@G@@        0,X11             .   @^@@@UPRTAQX11  +         0   @^@@@UPRTHQXQS
)@@G@@11  +         0   @F@@@UP$COMN    . LMJ 10,P$COMN  ENTER WITH A0 CONTAINQT
)@@G@@ING WORDS/LINE    @H@@@U          LA        A1,N$WSAV        . LOAD THE QU
)@@G@@NUMBER WORDS LEFT TO PRINT    @E@@@U          JZ        A1,0,10         QV
)@@G@@ . NO MORE WORDS  EXIT  @H@@@U          ANU       A1,A0            . SUBQW
)@@G@@TRACT THE NUMBER ON NEXT LINE-IN A2 @G@@@U          JP        A2,P$C1   QX
)@@G@@       . WILL BE MORE LEFT AFTER THIS LINE@F@@@U          SZ        N$WSQY
)@@G@@AV           . ALL DONE AFTER NEXT LINE   @H@@@U          LA        A0,AQZ
)@@G@@1            . LOAD NUMBER OF WORDS THAT WERE LEFT    @E@@@U          J RA
)@@G@@        1,10             . GO BACK TO WRITE OUT @D@@@UP$C1      SA      RB
)@@G@@  A2,N$WSAV        . STORE REMAINDER@E@@@U          J         1,10      RC
)@@G@@       . GO BACK TO WRITE OUT @D@@@UHDR       NOP                       RD
)@@G@@ . HEADER ROUTINE @I@@@U          SLJ       QGETAD           . GET THE ARE
)@@G@@DDRESS IN THE TABLE OF THIS FILE    @I@@@U          SA        A0,SAVADR RF
)@@G@@        . ADDRESS OF FILE INFORMATIOM        . 3B     @D@@@U          DLRG
)@@G@@        A0,0,A0          . LOAD FILENAME  @D@@@U          DS        A0,FRH
)@@G@@$NAM         . STORE IN PACKET@I@@@U          LA        A0,SAVADR       RI
)@@G@@  . ADDRESS OF FILE INFORMATION        . 3B     @D@Y@U          LA      RJ
)@@G@@  A0,3,A0          . LOAD FILENUMBER@D@@@Y          LA,H2     A0,3,A0   RK
)@@G@@       . LOAD FILENUMBER@G@@@U          E$BD      6,F$NO,3         . EDIRL
)@@G@@T FILE NUMBER TO PRINT PACKET @I@@@U          LA        A0,SAVADR       RM
)@@G@@  . ADDRESS OF FILE INFORMATION        . 3B     @E@@@U          LA      RN
)@@G@@  A0,2,A0          . LOAD BLOCK COUNT     @G@@@U          E$BD      6,B$RO
)@@G@@LOCK,6       . EDIT BLOCK COUNT TO PRINT PACKET @F@@@U          LA,H2   RP
)@@G@@  A0,NOWDS$        . LOAD BLOCK SIZE IN WORDS   @F@@@U          E$BD    RQ
)@@G@@  6,S$IZE,6        . CONVERT AND STORE IN PACKET@C@@@U          LA,H2   RR
)@@G@@  A0,NOWDS$        . RELOAD   @G@@@U          MSI,U     A0,6            RS
)@@G@@ . COMPUTE NUMBER OF CHARACTERS     @E@@@U          LA,S3     A2,NOWDS$ RT
)@@G@@       . SEE IF THERE WAS AN  @C@@@U          TE,U      A2,04           RU
)@@G@@ . AFC ERROR@D@@@U          J         CHAR             . NO, KEEP GOING RV
)@@G@@@G@@@U          LA,U      A1,6             . YES, REDUCE NUMBER OF CHARARW
)@@G@@CTERS @G@@@U          AN,S1     A1,NOWDS$        . WHERE TPRD$ STORED AFRX
)@@G@@C COUNT     @H@@@U          AN        A0,A1            . SUBTRACT CHARS RY
)@@G@@NOT READ FOR LAST WORD  @F@@@UCHAR      E$BD      6,C$HARS,6       . CONRZ
)@@G@@VERT AND STORE IN PACKET@E@@@U          LA        A0,P$PKT         . LOASA
)@@G@@D HEADER LINE     @D@@@U          ER        PRINT$           . WRITE IT SB
)@@G@@OUT   @C@@@U          J         *HDR             . GO BACK  @]@@@XXOPT  SC
)@@G@@    . @E@@@X          LA        A3,TEMP           . LOAD OPTION WORD    SD
)@@G@@@E@@@X          TOP,U     A3,04             . TEST FOR X OPTION ON@D@@@XSE
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . OK JUST DO IT @H@@@X          TGSF
)@@G@@        A0,A1             . IS LINE LENGTH > NO WORDS IN BUF?     @C@@@XSG
)@@G@@          LA        A0,A1             . NO , YES@C@@@X          J       SH
)@@G@@  0,X11             . GO BACK @]@@@U$(0)  .     @^@@@USAVEX10   +       SI
)@@G@@  0   @B@@@UH$DR1     'FILE  '                   .    @ @@@UF$NAM  '    SJ
)@@G@@        '        .@B@@@UF$NO      'NO.   '                   .    @ @@@USK
)@@G@@          '      '           .@^@@@U          'BLOCK NO.   '@ @@@UB$LOCKSL
)@@G@@    '      '           .@ @@@U          '      '           .@ @@@U      SM
)@@G@@    'SIZE ='           .@ @@@US$IZE     '      '           .@^@@@U      SN
)@@G@@    ' WORDS  OR  '@ @@@UC$HARS    '      '           .@ @@@U          ' SO
)@@G@@CHARS'           .@B@@@UC$TR      +         0                .    @B@@@USP
)@@G@@N$WSAV    +         0                .    @#@@@USAVADR    + 0     @F@@@USQ
)@@G@@W$ORD     +         0                 . SAVE AREA FOR EDITED WORD @B@@@USR
)@@G@@RANGE     +         037               .   @B@@@U          +         0176SS
)@@G@@              .   @ @@@UPF        FORM      12,6,18   @G@@@UAEPRINT   PFST
)@@G@@        1,30,AEBUF        . PRINT CONTROL WORD FOR ASCII    @B@@@UAEDITPSU
)@@G@@KT* A$EPKT    31,AEBUF          .   @B@@@UAEBUF*    RES       31        SV
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@UONEBLOCK* +         1,BLOCK           .   @B@@@UP$    SW
)@@G@@  FORM     12,6,18             .    @B@@@UP$PKT   P$ 2,15,H$DR1         SX
)@@G@@       .    @^@@@U          RES       10  @B@@@U         END            SY
)@@G@@             .    ___@@U          SA,Q2     A0,W*[S@@@*SDFF*@H@@@@. SCANSZ
)@@G@@    . REENTRANT ROUTINE TO SCAN A CARD PULLING ONE FIELD(1-12 CHARS) AT TA
)@@G@@@E@@@@          . A TIME. FIELDS MUST BE SPERATED FBY A ' ' OR ','@C@@@@TB
)@@G@@          . THE CALLING SEQUENCE IS AS FOLLOWS  @]@@@@          . @]@@@@TC
)@@G@@          . @A@@@@          .         LMJ 11,SCAN     @F@@@@          . TD
)@@G@@        +    1,CARD . IF A2 = NONZERO , NOT NEW CARD  @E@@@@          . TE
)@@G@@        +    0   2F A2=0, NCW CARD IS ASSUMED   @G@@@@          .       TF
)@@G@@  +    0   THE PARAMETER AREA IS FOR TEMP STORAGE FOR @H@@@@          . TG
)@@G@@        +    0   SCAN AND MUST NOT BE DESTROYED BY USER PROGRAM   @ @@@@TH
)@@G@@          .         +    0    @G@@@@          . CONTROL RETURNS WITH A2=TI
)@@G@@NO CHARS IN FIELD AND FIELD IN A0,A1@G@@@@          . RIGHT JUSTIFIED SPTJ
)@@G@@ACE FILLED TO LEFT. IF NO CHARS=0, THERE  @G@@@@          . ARE NO MORE TK
)@@G@@FIELDS IN CARD AND USER MUST SUPPLY NEW CARD    @C@@@@          .       TL
)@@G@@  UPON NEXT ENTRY TO SCAN     @I@@@@          . THIS ROUTINE IS  REENTRATM
)@@G@@NT AND DESTROYS X11-A5,R1-R3****************    @]@@@@          . @I@@@@TN
)@@G@@          AXR$                       . CALL SYSTEM PROCS                TO
)@@G@@  CPD01A    @I@@@@$(1)  . CHANGE TO CREATE I-BANK                       TP
)@@G@@                    CPD002    @^@@@@U         EQU       14  @^@@@@X11   TQ
)@@G@@    EQU       11  @I@@@@. PARAMETER TABLE IN USER PROGRAM LOOKS LIKE THITR
)@@G@@S (PROVIDED HE DONT CLOBBER IT)     @A@@@@.         +         1,CARDADDRTS
)@@G@@ESS   @A@@@@.         +         CHAR SAVE FOR   @A@@@@.         +       TT
)@@G@@  FIELD ASSEMBLY  @D@@@@.         +         NOCHRS,CHRPTR,NOTUSED,CTR,NOTU
)@@G@@TUSED @F@@@@.         +         WORD POINTER IN CARD AREA . INITIALLY 1,TV
)@@G@@CARD  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@STCWD     EQUF      1,11            TW
)@@G@@   CHAR SAVE AREA WHILE ASSEMBLING FIELD  @D@@@@CHRPTR    EQUF      3,11TX
)@@G@@,S3            . 5 INITIALLY  @E@@@@WDPTR     EQUF      4,11            TY
)@@G@@   . 1,CARD INITIALLLY  @E@@@@NOCHRS    EQUF      3,11,T1            . ITZ
)@@G@@NITIALLY SET TO 80@ @@@@CTR       EQUF      3,11,S5   @ @@@@LC        L,UA
)@@G@@S6      A5,0,*A1  @A@@@@I         DO     5 , L,S6+I A5,0,A1 @ @@@@SPACESUB
)@@G@@    +         '      '  @I@@@@LEAD      +         '      '         . WORUC
)@@G@@D TO HOLD PREVIOUS CHARACTER    CPD002    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@SCAN*     L UD
)@@G@@        A5,SPACES @^@@@@          TZ        A2  @ @@@@          J       UE
)@@G@@  NOTNEW    @E@@@@INIT      . ROUTINE TO INIT IALIZE SCAN, DESTROYS A5,AUF
)@@G@@4     @ @@@@          S         A5,CHRPTR @I@@@@          SA        A5,LUG
)@@G@@EAD          .                                    CPD002    @^@@@@      UH
)@@G@@   MSI,U     A4,6 @ @@@@          S         A4,NOCHRS @ @@@@          L UI
)@@G@@        A4,0,11   @ @@@@          S         A4,WDPTR  @I@@@@          SZUJ
)@@G@@        PERIOD           . ZERO OUT SCAN-STOP FLAG            CPD002    UK
)@@G@@@E@@@@NOTNEW    L         R3,NOCHRS          . 80 IF NEW CARD     @E@@@@UL
)@@G@@          S         A5,STCWD           . SET FIELD TO SPACES@ @@@@      UM
)@@G@@    S         A5,STCWD+1@G@@@@          SZ        CTR                . SUN
)@@G@@ET NO CHAR THIS FIELD YET     @I@@@@          LA        A0,PERIOD       UO
)@@G@@ . SET UP TEST FOR SCAN-STOP          CPD002    @I@@@@          TE,U    UP
)@@G@@  A0,0             . SHOULD WE STOP?                    CPD002    @I@@@@UQ
)@@G@@          J         DONE             . YES                              UR
)@@G@@  CPD002    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@GNC       . ROUTINE TO GET NEXUS
)@@G@@T CHARACTER FROM CARD USES A0,A1    @B@@@@          .         R3 CONTAINUT
)@@G@@S NO CHARS  @I@@@@          SA,S6     A5,LEAD          . STORE THE PREVIUU
)@@G@@OUS CHARACTER       CPD002    @ @@@@          JGD       R3,$+2    @D@@@@UV
)@@G@@          J         DONE               . CARD DONE    @ @@@@          L UW
)@@G@@        A0,CHRPTR @ @@@@          L         A1,WDPTR  @ @@@@          EXUX
)@@G@@        LC,A0     @ @@@@          JGD       A0,$+2    @^@@@@          L,UY
)@@G@@U       A0,5@ @@@@          S         A0,CHRPTR @ @@@@          S       UZ
)@@G@@  A1,WDPTR  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@.         CHARACTER NOW IN A5, CHECK FOR 'VA
)@@G@@ ', ',' OR '.'                  CPD01A    @[@@@@.     @I@@@@          TEVB
)@@G@@,U      A5,'.'           . TEST FOR PERIOD                    CPD002    VC
)@@G@@@I@@@@          J         BLK              . NO                         VD
)@@G@@        CPD002    @I@@@@          LA        A9,LEAD          . YES      VE
)@@G@@                          CPD002    @I@@@@          TE        A9,SPACES VF
)@@G@@       . WAS PREVIOUS CHARACTER A BLANK?    CPD002    @I@@@@          J VG
)@@G@@        GNC              . NO, IGNORE THIS PERIOD             CPD002    VH
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LR,U      R3,0             . YES, STOP SCAN             VI
)@@G@@        CPD002    @I@@@@          SA        A5,PERIOD        . SET FLAG VJ
)@@G@@TO STOP FUTURE SCANS      CPD002    @I@@@@          J         DONE      VK
)@@G@@       .                                    CPD002    @I@@@@BLK       TEVL
)@@G@@,U      A5,5             . WAS IT A BLANK?                    CPD002    VM
)@@G@@@ @@@@          J         NOSPCE    @H@@@@          TNZ       CTR       VN
)@@G@@         . HAVE WE HAD A CHAR YET THIS CARD     @E@@@@          J       VO
)@@G@@  GNC                NO IGNORE THIS SPACE @^@@@@         J         DONE VP
)@@G@@@I@@@@NOSPCE    TE,U     A5,','            . TEST FOR COMMA             VQ
)@@G@@        CPD01A    @I@@@@          J        PNC               . GO TO VALVR
)@@G@@ID CHARACTER ROUTINE      CPD01A    @^@@@@         J         DONE @[@@@@VS
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PNC       . ROUTINE TO STORE A CHAR DEXTROYS A4,VT
)@@G@@A5,A3 @A@@@@          . ENTER WITH CHAR IN A5   @ @@@@          L       VU
)@@G@@  A4,STCWD+1@ @@@@          L         A3,STCWD  @ @@@@          DSC     VV
)@@G@@  A3,66     @ @@@@          S         A3,STCWD  @ @@@@          S       VW
)@@G@@  A4,STCWD+1@ @@@@          S,S6      A5,STCWD+1@ @@@@          L       VX
)@@G@@  A4,CTR    @^@@@@          A,U       A4,1@ @@@@          S         A4,CVY
)@@G@@TR    @^@@@@          J         GNC @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@DONE  VZ
)@@G@@    S         R3,NOCHRS @F@@@@          L         A2,CTR             COUWA
)@@G@@NT OF CHARS THIS FIELD  @ @@@@          L         A0,STCWD  @ @@@@      WB
)@@G@@    L         A1,STCWD+1@^@@@@          J        5,11 @#@@@@           EWC
)@@G@@ND    ___TR   A3,STCWD  *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@       AXR$ @G@@@@X         PRWD
)@@G@@OC      . CALL IS EDIT MAX WORDS,CHARS/WORD,CNTINC,TYPE     @#@@@@EDIT* WE
)@@G@@    NAME    @#@@@@ENT*      NOP     @I@@@@          SLJ       HDR       WF
)@@G@@       . PRINTS FILENAME, NR, BLOCK NR, AND BLOCK SIZE@E@@@@          SZWG
)@@G@@        C$TR             . LINE NR ON PRINTOUT  @B@@@@          L,U     WH
)@@G@@  A0,2             .    @ @@@@          S,H2      A0,P$ED3+1@A@@@@      WI
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,BLOCK-X(1,1) @ @@@@          S,H2      A0,P$ED3  @E@@@@WJ
)@@G@@          L,H2      A0,NOWDS$        . NR WORDS IN RECORD   @G@@@@      WK
)@@G@@    S         A0,N$WSAV        . NR WORDS IN RECORD LEFT TO PRINT @E@@@@WL
)@@G@@L$OOP     L,U       A0,X(1,1)      .LOAD MAX NO WDS IN LINE @I@@@@      WM
)@@G@@    SLJ       XOPT           . IF X OPT DECREASE TOT NR WDS TO PRNT 1 LIWN
)@@G@@NE    @I@@@@          LMJ       10,P$COMN      . NR WDS TO PRNT IN A0, DWO
)@@G@@ECR N$WSAV BY WDS PRNTD @I@@@@          J         *ENT  .          . RETWP
)@@G@@URN HERE  FROM P$COMN IF N$WSAV = 0-NO PRT@I@@@@          S,S3      A0,PWQ
)@@G@@$ED2       . STORE NO WORDS INTO RPT FUNCTION PRM 2 14-11   @F@@@@      WR
)@@G@@    L,H2      A0,P$ED3         . ADDR STARTED LAST PRINT AT @F@@@@      WS
)@@G@@    A,U       A0,X(1,1)      . UPDATE M BY NO WORDS PER LINE@G@@@@      WT
)@@G@@    S,H2      A0,P$ED3         . STARTING ADDR OF WORDS TO PRINT  @H@@@@WU
)@@G@@          E$OUT                    . CALL INTERREPTIVE ROUTINE PRM 2 14-WV
)@@G@@10    @E@@@@          E$O       4,15,C$TR        . PUT IN OCTAL LINE NR WW
)@@G@@@I@@@@P$ED2     E$RPT     X(1,2),X(1,1),1  . REPEAT EDIT FUNC NR WORDS TWX
)@@G@@IMES PRM 2 1413   @A@@@@P$ED3     .         EDITING FUNCTION@G@@@@      WY
)@@G@@   DO   X(1,4)=1 , E$A 6,1,BLOCK-16       . ALPHA OR HOLLERITH    @I@@@@WZ
)@@G@@         DO    X(1,4)=2 , E$O 20,36,BLOCK-8     . OCTAL PRT PSN 20,FULL XA
)@@G@@WD,START BK-@B@@@@         DO    X(1,4)=3 , E$A 6,1,BLOCK-16@I@@@@      XB

)@@G@@LN    @ @@@@          L,U       A0,X(1,3) @E@@@@          A         A0,CXD
)@@G@@$TR          . UP LINE WORD COUNTER @ @@@@          S         A0,C$TR   XE
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L,U       A0,1             . RESTORE M ADDRESS    @B@@@@XF
)@@G@@          S,H2      A0,P$ED3+1       .    @ @@@@          J         L$OOXG
)@@G@@P     @I@@@@XOPT      NOP                        .                      XH
)@@G@@              CPD002    @I@@@@          LA        A3,TEMP          .    XI
)@@G@@                                CPD002    @I@@@@          TOP,U     A3,0XJ
)@@G@@4            . 'X' OPTION SET?                    CPD002    @I@@@@      XK
)@@G@@    J         *XOPT            . NO                                 CPD0XL
)@@G@@02    @I@@@@          TG        A0,N$WSAV        . YES, ARE THE # OF WORXM
)@@G@@DS IN THE     CPD002    @I@@@@                                     . RECXN
)@@G@@ORD > THE MAX # OF WORDS PER LINCPD002    @E@@@@          J         *XOPXO
)@@G@@T            . NO, PROCESS NORMALLY @I@@@@          SA        A0,N$WSAV XP
)@@G@@       . YES, REDUCE TO NOE LINE OF PRINT   CPD002    @I@@@@          J XQ
)@@G@@        *XOPT            . NOW GO BACK                        CPD002    XR
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @]@@@@E PROC 1,2. @G@@@@E$BD* NAME EBD$X        XS
)@@G@@             . PROC-BINARY TO FIELDDATA DECIMAL @F@@@@E$BO* NAME EBO$X  XT

)@@G@@ARAMETERS ARE ALREADY SE. 03D @H@@@@          LA        A8,A0           ES

)@@G@@J       QGETAD            . GET FILE DATA                   . 03D @I@@@@FC
)@@G@@          LA        A1,2,A0           . DRPKT+5                         FD
)@@G@@. 03D   D VA@H@@@@          SA        A1,2,A0           . SAVE IT AWAY  FE

)@@G@@  PRT                                                 . 03D @H@@@@. ALPHFI
)@@G@@A PRINT ROUTINE    WORDS SEPERATED                                . 03D FJ
)@@G@@@H@@@@PRTAQ*    .                                                       FK
)@@G@@      . 03D @H@@@@          SX        X11,PRTAQX11      .               FL
)@@G@@                  . 03D @H@@@@          SLJ       HDR               . PRFM

)@@G@@        . CLEAR OCTAL LINE COUNTER        . 03D @H@@@@          LA      FO

)@@G@@    TNZ       A0                . IF NONE QUIT YOU TURKEY         . 03D FQ

)@@G@@      . 03D @H@@@@          LA,U      A1,20             . LENGTH OF LINEFS

)@@G@@        . SUBTRACT ONE FOR THE GREAT JGD  . 03D @H@@@@          LR      FV
)@@G@@  R2,A0             . OK HERE WE GO                   . 03D @H@@@@      FW
)@@G@@    LX        X10,ONEBLOCK     . SET FOR LOOP INDEXING            . 03D FX
)@@G@@@H@@@@          SX        X10,SAVEX10                                   FY

)@@G@@DITOR             . 03D @H@@@@          A$EOCTF    4,C$TR            . PGA

)@@G@@        .                                 . 03D @H@@@@          A,U     GC
)@@G@@  A0,20         . ADD INCREMENT                       . 03D @H@@@@      GD

)@@G@@0       .                                 . 03D @H@@@@          DL      GJ
)@@G@@  A1,RANGE          . 037,0176                        . 03D @H@@@@      GK

)@@G@@@[@@@@      @A@@@@              @ADD LISP*LIB.STRTPLNR@[@@@@      @G@@@@FS
)@@G@@THIS WILL START LISP RUNNING, CHANGE THE COMMENT CHARACTER FROM '?' TO  FT
)@@G@@@F@@@@';', LOAD IN THE COMPILED VERSIONS OF PLNR, PRETTYP AND EDIT, DO AFU
)@@G@@@G@@@@(GROW 30) TO GET YOU SOME MORE CORE, AND THEN DO A (PLNR) TO GET PFV
)@@G@@LNR   @F@@@@RUNNING.  YOU WILL THEN BE COMMUNICATING WITH A NEW LEVEL OFFW
)@@G@@ LISP @F@@@@SUPERVISION WHICH ACTS AS A READ-THVAL-PRINT LOOP (INSTEAD OFX
)@@G@@F THE @G@@@@NORMAL READ-EVAL-PRINT).  ALL LISP CONTROL CARDS ARE RECOGNIFY
)@@G@@ZED, EXCEPT @G@@@@THAT A RETURN TO THE SUPERVISOR RETURNS YOU TO THE PLNFZ
)@@G@@R SUPERVISOR (E.G.@G@@@@IF YOU GET INTO TROUBLE, :LISP WILL RETURN YOU TGA
)@@G@@O PLNR).  YOU MAY RETURN@G@@@@TO THE NORMAL LISP SUPERVISOR VIA (RETURN GB
)@@G@@<EXPR>), AND MAY RE-ENTER PLNR@]@@@@VIA (PLNR). @[@@@@      @#@@@@PLNR PGC
)@@G@@RIMITIVES   @#@@@@---------------   @[@@@@      @G@@@@THIS SECTION DESCRGD
)@@G@@IBES THE PLNR PRIMITIVES WHICH ARE CURRENTLY AVAIL-   @G@@@@ABLE.  COMMEGE
)@@G@@NTS ARE APPENDED ONLY WHEN THERE ARE DIFFERENCES BETWEEN    @G@@@@THIS IGF
)@@G@@MPLEMENTATION AND MIT PLNR.  NOTE THAT META-LINGUISTIC VARIABLES  @G@@@@GG
)@@G@@ARE ENCLOSED IN ANGLE BRACKETS (<>), AND ARGUMENTS WHICH ARE EVALUATED  GH
)@@G@@@G@@@@BEFORE THE PRIMITIVE IS APPLIED ARE INDICATED BY PRECEDING THEM WIGI
)@@G@@TH    @^@@@@A QUOTE-SIGN ('<>).     @[@@@@      @[@@@@(PLNR)@G@@@@      GJ
)@@G@@   THIS FUNCTION ENTERS A NEW LEVEL OF PLNR SUPERVISION, JUST     @G@@@@GK
)@@G@@         AS (LISP) ENTERS A NEW LEVEL OF LISP SUPERVISION.  YOU MAY     GL
)@@G@@@G@@@@         RETURN FROM PLNR TO LISP (VIA [RETURN]), AND THEN RE-ENTEGM
)@@G@@R     @D@@@@         PLNR WITHOUT AFFECTING THE PLNR DATA BASE.   @[@@@@GN

)@@G@@L)] [(THSUCCEED)])@[@@@@      @A@@@@(THNV <VARIABLE>)  ::  $=<VARIABLE> JO
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @^@@@@(THOR <E1> <E2> ...)    @[@@@@      @A@@@@(THPRETTYP 'JP
)@@G@@<THM-NAMES> '<FILE>)    @[@@@@      @G@@@@         THE LIST OF PLNR THEOJQ
)@@G@@REMS INDICATED BY <THM-NAMES> WILL BE     @G@@@@         PRETTYPRINTED TJR
)@@G@@O THE DATA-FILE <FILE> (IF <FILE> IS ABSENT     @B@@@@         THEY ARE JS
)@@G@@PRINTED ON THE TTY).    @[@@@@      @A@@@@(THPROG <VAR-DECLARATIONS> <BOJT
)@@G@@DY>)  @[@@@@      @ @@@@(THPUT '<ATR> '<IND> '<VALUE>)@[@@@@      @A@[@@JU
)@@G@@         (1108 LISP ARGUMENT ORDER) @A@@@[         (1110 LISP ARGUMENT OJV
)@@G@@RDER) @[@@@@      @A@@@@(THPUTPROP '<ATR> '<VALUE> '<IND>)  @[@@@@      JW
)@@G@@@ @@@@(THREMPROP '<ATR> '<IND>)     @[@@@@      @F@@@@(THRESTRICT <PLNR-JX
)@@G@@VAR> <LISP-FN1> <LISP-FN2> ...)  ::  ($R ...)   @[@@@@      @D@@@@(THRETJY
)@@G@@URN '<EXPR>)  ::  (THSUCCEED THPROG '<EXPR>)    @[@@@@      @A@@@@(THRPLJZ
)@@G@@ACA '<DOTTED-PAIR> '<NEW-CAR>)@[@@@@      @A@@@@(THRPLACD '<DOTTED-PAIR>KA
)@@G@@ '<NEW-CDR>)@[@@@@      @B@@@@(THSETQ <VAR1> '<E1> <VAR2> '<E2> ...)    KB
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @ @@@@(THSTATE <IND1> <IND2> ...)   @[@@@@      @E@@@@      KC
)@@G@@   (THSTATE) :: (THSTATE THASSERTION $TC $TA $TE)     @[@@@@      @ @@@@KD
)@@G@@(THSUCCEED <ARG1> <ARG2>)     @[@@@@      @^@@@@         (THSUCCEED)    KE
)@@G@@@D@@@@         (THSUCCEED THTAG <TAG>)  ::  (THGO <TAG>)    @D@@@@      KF
)@@G@@   (THSUCCEED THPROG '<E>)  ::  (THRETURN '<E>) @ @@@@         (THSUCCEEKG
)@@G@@D THPROG)   @G@@@@         (THSUCCEED THEOREM '<E>)     CAUSES THE CURREKH
)@@G@@NT THEOREM TO     @G@@@@         (THSUCCEED THEOREM)          SUCCEED, EKI
)@@G@@VEN IF THERE ARE NESTED @C@@@@                                      THPRKJ
)@@G@@OGS.  @[@@@@      @ @@@@(THTRACE <IND1> <IND2> ...)   @[@@@@      @ @@@@KK
)@@G@@         <INDS> :: <ATOM>     @C@@@@                   (<ATOM> <TRACE PRKL
)@@G@@EDICATE>)   @F@@@@                   (<ATOM> <TRACE PREDICATE> <BREAK PRKM
)@@G@@EDICATE>)   @E@@@@         <ATOM> :: <THM-NAME>, THEOREM, $G, $A, $E, THKN
)@@G@@BKPT  @[@@@@      @G@@@@         [THBREAK] IS USED IF THE <BREAK PREDICAKO
)@@G@@TE> EVALS TO NON-NIL.   @C@@@@         TYPE T TO EXIT FROM THE BREAK LOOKP
)@@G@@P.    @[@@@@      @A@@@@(THUNTRACE <ATOM1> <ATOM2> ...)     @[@@@@      KQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@         (THUNTRACE) :: UNTRACE EVERYTHING THAT'S TRACED    @[@@@@KR
)@@G@@      @A@@@@(THUNIQUE '<EXPR1> '<EXPR2> ...)    @[@@@@      @A@@@@(THV <KS
)@@G@@VARIABLE>)  ::  $?<VARIABLE>  @[@@@@      @^@@@@(THVAL '<EXPR> '<ALIST>)KT
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @^@@@@(THVDO <E1> <E2> ...)   @[@@@@      @G@@@@         THIKU
)@@G@@S NEW PRIMITIVE ACTS LIKE THDO, EXCEPT IT IS NOT UNDONE     @C@@@@      KV
)@@G@@   ON FAILURE BACKUP.  IT IS EQUIVALENT TO@[@@@@      @G@@@@            KW
)@@G@@  (THPROG NIL (THDO <E1> <E2> ...) (THFINALIZE THPROG))     @[@@@@      KX
)@@G@@@B@@@@(THVSETQ <VAR1> '<E1> <VAR2> '<E2> ...)   @[@@@@      @#@@@@ABBREVKY
)@@G@@IATIONS     @#@@@@-------------     @[@@@@      @G@@@@THE FOLLOWING ABBRKZ
)@@G@@EVIATIONS MAY BE USED TO SAVE YOUR THFINGERS FROM     @ @@@@TYPING MANY LA
)@@G@@LONG THNAMES:     @[@@@@      @ @@@@         $?<X> :: (THV <X>)   @ @@@@LB
)@@G@@         $=<X> :: (THNV <X>)  @ @@@@         $&<X> :: (THEV <X>)  @ @@@@LC
)@@G@@         $N<N> :: (THANUM <N>)@A@@@@         $T    :: (THTBF THTRUE)    LD
)@@G@@@^@@@@         $G    :: THGOAL@ @@@@         $A    :: THASSERT    @ @@@@LE
)@@G@@         $AL   :: THASSERTLIST@ @@@@         $E    :: THERASE     @ @@@@LF
)@@G@@         $R    :: THRESTRICT  @ @@@@         $TC   :: THCONSE     @^@@@@LG
)@@G@@         $TA   :: THANTE@ @@@@         $TE   :: THERASING   @[@@@@      LH
)@@G@@@^@@@@THSTUFF YOU SHOULD KNOW @^@@@@----------------------- @[@@@@      LI
)@@G@@@G@[@@MOST PLNR ERROR MESSAGES ARE DESCRIBED IN (1).  NOTE, HOWEVER, THALJ
)@@G@@T 1108@G@@@[MOST PLNR ERROR MESSAGES ARE DESCRIBED IN (1).  NOTE, HOWEVELK
)@@G@@R, THAT 1110@G@@@@PLNR SIMPLY THFAILS BACK TO THE PLNR SUPERVISOR AFTER LL
)@@G@@AN ERROR OCCURS.  @[@@@@      @F@@@@ALL PLNR VARIABLES ($?<X> OR $=<X>) LM
)@@G@@MUST BE BOUND BEFORE THEY ARE @F@@@@REFERENCED, EITHER BY APPEARING IN ALN
)@@G@@ <VAR-DECLARATIONS> LIST IN A @G@@@@THEOREM, THPROG, THFIND OR THMESSAGELO
)@@G@@, OR BY EXPLICITLY CREATING A GLOBAL@C@@@@BINDING (E.G., (THSETQ $?X 'THLP
)@@G@@UNASSIGNED)).     @[@@@@      @G@@@@LISP EXPRESSIONS MAY BE USED WITH RELQ
)@@G@@LATIVE IMPUNITY WITHIN PLNR EXPRES- @G@@@@SIONS  -  THE RULE IS THAT IF LR
)@@G@@IT EVALS TO NIL IT FAILS (LIKE (THFAIL)), @G@@@@OTHERWISE IT SUCCEEDS.  LS
)@@G@@TO EVALUATE A LISP EXPRESSION WHICH RETURNS A   @F@@@@VALUE OF NIL WITHOLT
)@@G@@UT FAILING, YOU MUST THEREFORE DO SOMETHING LIKE@A@@@@(THDO <EXPR>) OR (LU
)@@G@@DO <EXPR> T).     @[@@@@      @F@@@@NOTE, HOWEVER, THAT COMPLEX PLNR PRILV
)@@G@@MITIVES SHOULD NEVER BE PLACED@G@@@@INSIDE OF A LISP EXPRESSION.  FOR EXLW
)@@G@@AMPLE, A [COND] MAY APPEAR IN A     @F@@@@THPROG, BUT IT MAY NOT CONTAINLX
)@@G@@ ANY THGOALS (USE [THCOND] INSTEAD).@F@@@@SIMPLE PLNR PRIMITIVES LIKE [TLY
)@@G@@HV] AND [THASVAL] MAY APPEAR IN LISP@G@@@@EXPRESSIONS (E.G., (PRINT $?X)LZ
)@@G@@ IS OK).  WHEN IN DOUBT, YOU MAY ALWAYS   @^@@@@DO AN EXPLICIT $&<EXPR>.MA
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @G@@@@SINCE PLNR MAKES RATHER EXTENSIVE USE OF THE QUESTION-MB
)@@G@@MARK CHARACTER,   @G@@@@THE LISP COMMENT CHARACTER IS CHANGED TO SEMI-COMC
)@@G@@LON WHEN PLNR IS LOADED.@F@@@@YOU MAY TEMPORARILY CHANGE IT BACK TO '?' MD
)@@G@@(E.G., TO @ADD IN SOME  @B@@@@CODE THAT CONTAINS COMMENTS) BY TYPING:   ME
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @B@@@@         (READMAC "?" (READMAC ";" F))    @A@@@@      MF
)@@G@@   (DELIM "?" (DELIM ";" F))  @[@@@@      @^@@@@USER, MEET PLNR ...     MG
)@@G@@@^@@@@-------------------     @[@@@@      @G@@@@THE BEST WAY TO GET FAMIMH
)@@G@@LIAR WITH AN INTERACTIVE PROGRAMMING SYSTEM IS  @G@@@@TO SIT DOWN AND PLMI
)@@G@@AY WITH IT FOR AWHILE.  AS A PRELIMINARY INTRODUCTION @G@@@@TO THE USAGEMJ
)@@G@@ OF PLNR, TRY THE FOLLOWING CONVERSATION (DESCRIBED MORE    @#@@@@FULLY MK
)@@G@@IN (1)):    @[@@@@      @^@@@@@ADD LISP*LIB.STRTPLNR  @B@@@@         ;(WML
)@@G@@AIT FOR THVAL: TO APPEAR)     @[@@@@      @^@@@@($A (HUMAN TURING))     MM
)@@G@@@ @@@@         ;TURING IS HUMAN     @[@@@@      @B@@@@($TC (X) (FALLIBLEMN
)@@G@@ $?X) ($G (HUMAN $?X))) @A@@@@         ;ALL HUMANS ARE FALLIBLE   @[@@@@MO
)@@G@@      @^@@@@($G (FALLIBLE TURING))  @ @@@@         ;IS TURING FALLIBLE? MP
)@@G@@@G@@@@         ;NO?  AHA - WE FORGOT TO TELL PLNR TO USE AVAILABLE THEORMQ
)@@G@@EMS   @[@@@@      @ @@@@($G (FALLIBLE TURING) $T)     @^@@@@         ;THMR

)@@G@@RN $?Y))    @A@@@@         ;IS ANYTHING FALLIBLE?     @[@@@@      @G@@@@MT
)@@G@@[THDO ($A (HUMAN SOCRATES)) ($A (GREEK SOCRATES)) ($A (HUMAN NEWTON]    MU

)@@G@@AL/I--GL/I--GL3I-\I[3^@)@D@@@@DESCRIPTION OF LISP ARITHMETIC PACKAGE  - IW
)@@G@@ 8/14/73    @D@@@@--------------------------------------------------    IX
)@@G@@@@@@@@@G@@@@THIS PACKAGE PROVIDES SEVERAL FUNCTIONS WHICH MAKE IT A LITTIY
)@@G@@LE EASIER   @F@@@@TO DO ARITHMETIC IN LISP.  THESE FUNCTIONS RANGE FROM IZ
)@@G@@SIMPLE RE-  @G@@@@DEFINITIONS OF SOME OF THE STANDARD SYSTEM FUNCTIONS [JA
)@@G@@E.G., YOU CAN     @G@@@@SAY (- (- A B) C) INSTEAD OF (DIFFERENCE (DIFFERJB
)@@G@@ENCE A B) C)], TO AN    @G@@@@F-FORMAT OUTPUT ROUTINE.  MORE EXTENSIVE AJC
)@@G@@RITHMETIC CAPABILITIES MAY    @G@@@@BE ADDED AT A LATER DATE (E.G., PROVJD
)@@G@@IDING ACCESS TO THE FORTRAN LIBRARY @G@@@@ROUTINES).  WHEN AND IF THIS IJE
)@@G@@S DONE WILL DEPEND ON THE EXPRESSED NEEDS @^@@@@OF THE USER COMMUNITY.  JF
)@@G@@@@@@@@@D@@@@THE ARITHMETIC PACKAGE IS LOADED BY TYPING (IN LISP): @@@@@@JG
)@@G@@@F@@@@        @ADD LISP*LIB.ARITH    OR    :EXEC @USE LISP,LISP*LIB     JH
)@@G@@@E@@@@                                     (LOAD '(LISP.ARITH))   @@@@@@JI
)@@G@@@D@@@@THE FUNCTIONS CURRENTLY AVAILABLE ARE DESCRIBED BELOW.@@@@@@@#@@@@JJ
)@@G@@+ - * / = GT LT   @#@@@@---------------   @@@@@@@G@@@@THE FOUR BASIC LISJK
)@@G@@P ARITHMETIC OPERATORS AND THREE OF THE PREDICATES    @G@@@@HAVE BEEN REJL
)@@G@@-NAMED TO MAKE THEM MORE CONVENIENT TO USE (THE OLD NAMES   @E@@@@ARE STJM
)@@G@@ILL AROUND FOR YOU LISP PURISTS).  THE NEW NAMES ARE: @@@@@@@^@@@@      JN
)@@G@@        NEW    OLD@^@@@@              ---    ---@@@@@@@ @@@@            JO
)@@G@@   +     PLUS     @A@@@@               -     DIFFERENCE     @ @@@@      JP
)@@G@@         *     TIMES    @ @@@@               /     QUOTIENT @ @@@@      JQ
)@@G@@         =     EQUAL    @ @@@@               GT    GREATERP @ @@@@      JR
)@@G@@         LT    LESSP    @@@@@@@C@@@@FOR EXAMPLE, THE FOLLOWING NONSENSE JS
)@@G@@STATEMENT:  @@@@@@@F@@@@              (COND [<EQUAL (DIFFERENCE 1 (QUOTIJT
)@@G@@ENT A B)) 0.5>    @A@@@@                      <TIMES A B>]  @E@@@@      JU
)@@G@@              [<GREATERP (PLUS (TIMES A B) 0.5) 10>   @B@@@@            JV
)@@G@@          <QUOTIENT A B>])    @@@@@@@A@@@@CAN ALSO BE WRITTEN AS FOLLOWSJW
)@@G@@:     @@@@@@@B@@@@              (COND [<= (- 1 (/ A B)) 0.5>@ @@@@      JX
)@@G@@                <* A B>]@C@@@@                    [<GT (+ (* A B) 0.5) 1JY
)@@G@@0>    @A@@@@                      </ A B>])     @@@@@@@]@@@@LE GE NE    JZ
)@@G@@@]@@@@--------    @@@@@@@F@@@@THESE NEW FUNCTIONS SUPPLEMENT THE ARITHMEKA
)@@G@@TIC PREDICATES, WITH THE@^@@@@OBVIOUS INTERPRETATIONS.@@@@@@@[@@@@**    KB
)@@G@@@[@@@@--    @@@@@@@G@@@@THIS NEW OPERATOR PERFORMS INTEGER EXPONENTIATIOKC
)@@G@@N.  (** N P) RAISES     @G@@@@N (INTEGER OR REAL) TO THE P (INTEGER GE 0KD
)@@G@@) POWER.  THIS IS PRIMARILY   @G@@@@OF USE IN CASES WHERE THE POWER TO WKE
)@@G@@HICH A NUMBER IS TO BE RAISED IS    @G@@@@UNKNOWN UNTIL RUN-TIME.  IF YOKF
)@@G@@U KNOW THAT YOU WANT TO COMPUTE N CUBED,  @G@@@@FOR EXAMPLE, IT IS MORE KG
)@@G@@EFFICIENT TO WRITE (* N N N) THAN (** N 3).     @A@@@@(** N P) WITH P NEKH
)@@G@@GATIVE RETURNS 1. @@@@@@@[@@@@ABS   @[@@@@---   @@@@@@@G@@@@(ABS N) RETUKI
)@@G@@RNS THE ABSOLUTE VALUE OF N (WHAT ELSE DID YOU EXPECT?).    @@@@@@@[@@@@KJ
)@@G@@FLOAT @[@@@@----- @@@@@@@G@@@@(FLOAT N), WHERE N IS AN OCTAL OR DECIMAL KK
)@@G@@INTEGER, RETURNS THE FLOAT-   @F@@@@ING POINT EQUIVALENT OF N.  IT IS DEKL
)@@G@@FINED SIMPLY AS (+ N 0.0).    @@@@@@@[@@@@OCTAL @[@@@@----- @@@@@@@F@@@@KM
)@@G@@(OCTAL N) RETURNS THE OCTAL VALUE OF WHATEVER N POINTS TO (I.E.,  @F@@@@KN
)@@G@@(OCTAL 10) RETURNS 12Q, AND (OCTAL 1.0) RETURNS 201400000000Q).   @@@@@@KO
)@@G@@@[@@@@EVENP @[@@@@----- @@@@@@@E@@@@(EVENP N) RETURNS T IF THE INTEGER NKP
)@@G@@ IS EVEN, NIL OTHERWISE.@@@@@@@]@@@@MAX / MIN   @]@@@@---------   @@@@@@KQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@(MAX N1 N2 ...) RETURNS THE LARGEST OF ITS ARGUMENTS. @D@@@@(MIN NKR
)@@G@@1 N2 ...) RETURNS THE SMALLEST OF ITS ARGUMENTS.@@@@@@@]@@@@FACTORIAL   KS
)@@G@@@]@@@@---------   @@@@@@@C@@@@(FACTORIAL N) RETURNS N FACTORIAL (SURPRISKT
)@@G@@E!).  @@@@@@@[@@@@FPRINT@[@@@@------@@@@@@@E@@@@THIS PRINTS A NUMBER IN KU
)@@G@@F-FORMAT.  THE CALLING SEQUENCE IS: @@@@@@@ @@@@              (FPRINT N KV
)@@G@@W D)  @@@@@@@G@@@@WHERE N IS A NUMBER (INTEGER OR REAL), W IS AN INTEGERKW
)@@G@@ GIVING THE TOTAL @G@@@@NUMBER OF PRINT POSITIONS TO USE, AND D IS AN INKX
)@@G@@TEGER GIVING THE NUMBER @G@@@@OF PLACES TO THE RIGHT OF THE DECIMAL PLACKY
)@@G@@E TO PRINT.  THE NUMBER WILL  @G@@@@BE ROUNDED AND PRINTED RIGHT-JUSTIFIKZ
)@@G@@ED IN THE W-CHARACTER FIELD WITH    @G@@@@BLANK FILL.  IF THE INTEGER POLA
)@@G@@RTION OF N (INCLUDING A MINUS SIGN IF     @G@@@@NECESSARY) WON'T FIT IN LB
)@@G@@W-D-1 SPACES, THE FIELD IS X-FILLED.  D MUST BE @G@@@@GE 0 AND W MUST BELC
)@@G@@ GE D+2.  NOTE:  FPRINT PRIN1'S THE NUMBER - TERPRI OR@C@@@@PRINT MUST BLD
)@@G@@E USED TO TERMINATE THE PRINT LINE. @@@@@@@D@@@@AS AN EXAMPLE OF THE USELE
)@@G@@ OF FPRINT, THE FOLLOWING:    @@@@@@@F@@@@              (DO (FPRINT 1.23LF
)@@G@@4E-3 10 5) (FPRINT -1.87E1 8 0))    @]@@@@WILL PRINT: @A@@@@            LG
)@@G@@     0.00123    -19.    @@@@@@@[@@@@IPRINT@[@@@@------@@@@@@@F@@@@THIS PLH
)@@G@@RINTS AN INTEGER IN I-FORMAT.  THE CALLING SEQUENCE IS:     @@@@@@@ @@@@LI
)@@G@@              (IPRINT N W)    @@@@@@@G@@@@WHERE N IS AN INTEGER AND W ISLJ
)@@G@@ THE NUMBER OF PRINT POSITIONS TO USE.    @G@@@@THE NUMBER WILL BE RIGHTLK
)@@G@@-JUSTIFIED IN THE W-CHARACTER FIELD WITH BLANK  @F@@@@FILL.  IF IT WON'TLL
)@@G@@ FIT, THE FIELD IS X-FILLED.  IPRINT USES PRIN1,@E@@@@SO TERPRI OR PRINTLM
)@@G@@ MUST BE USED TO TERMINATE THE PRINT LINE.@@@@@@@F@@@@ACTUALLY, THE ABOVLN
)@@G@@E IS ONLY HALF THE STORY.  ALTHOUGH INTENDED    @F@@@@PRIMARILY FOR USE LO
)@@G@@WITH INTEGERS, IPRINT WILL PRINT ANY LISP OBJECT@G@@@@RIGHT-JUSTIFIED INLP
)@@G@@ THE W-CHARACTER FIELD.  THUS (IPRINT 'ABC 10) WILL   @G@@@@PRINT SEVEN LQ
)@@G@@SPACES FOLLOWED BY 'ABC'.  (IPRINT N W) WHERE N IS REAL WILL@G@@@@PRINT LR
)@@G@@N RIGHT-JUSTIFIED IN THE W-CHARACTER FIELD, USING LISP'S STANDARD @^@@@@LS
)@@G@@E-FORMAT PRINT ROUTINE. @@@@@@@[@@@@OPRINT@[@@@@------@@@@@@@G@@@@THIS PLT
)@@G@@RINTS WHATEVER ITS FIRST ARGUMENT POINTS TO (EVEN IF IT IS NOT    @E@@@@LU
)@@G@@A NUMBER) AS AN OCTAL INTEGER.  THE CALLING SEQUENCE IS:    @@@@@@@ @@@@LV
)@@G@@              (OPRINT N W)    @@@@@@@G@@@@WHICH CAUSES (OCTAL N) TO BE PLW
)@@G@@RINTED RIGHT-JUSTIFIED IN A W-CHARACTER   @G@@@@FIELD.  (LIKE [FPRINT] ALX
)@@G@@ND [IPRINT], [OPRINT] USES [PRIN1] FOR PRINTING @G@@@@THE NUMBER).  IF WLY
)@@G@@ IS 12 OR LESS, ONLY THE RIGHT-MOST W OCTAL DIGITS OF @G@@@@N WILL BE PRLZ
)@@G@@INTED, WITH ZERO FILL ON THE LEFT IF NECESSARY.  IF N IS    @F@@@@GREATEMA
)@@G@@R THAN 12, A FULL TWELVE-DIGIT OCTAL NUMBER WILL BE PRINTED,@F@@@@PRECEDMB
)@@G@@ED BY W-12 BLANKS.  NOTE THAT [OPRINT] DOES NOT PRINT A 'Q' @^@@@@FOLLOWMC
)@@G@@ING THE NUMBER.   @@@@@@@[@@@@XPRINT@[@@@@------@@@@@@@G@@@@(XPRINT X N)MD
)@@G@@ PRIN1'S THE OBJECT X N TIMES.  THUS (XPRINT " " 10) SPACES @G@@@@OVER TME
)@@G@@EN SPACES AND (XPRINT "-" 72) DRAWS A LINE ACROSS THE TELETYPE    @B@@@@MF
)@@G@@PAGE.  IF N IS LE 0, NO PRINTING OCCURS.  @@@@@@___ NUMBER).  IF W IS 12MG
)@@G@@ OR LESS, ONLY THE RIGHT-MOST W OCTAL DIGITS OF @G@@@@N WILL BE PRINTED,MH
)@@G@@ WITH ZERO FILL ON THE L*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@(DO   @^@@@@(CSETQ MAPCAR MAPCMI

)@@G@@@^@@@@XT      EQU        001  @^@@@@XF      EQU        002  @^@@@@XC    SX

)@@G@@CTRCHR  EQU        ':'  @^@@@@/. COMMON LISP MACROS   @^@@@@. LOAD VALUETI
)@@G@@ REGISTER   @]@@@@LOAD*   PROC@ @@@@I       EQU        LOAD(1,1)  @A@@@@TJ
)@@G@@J       EQU        (I=0)++(I>16)    @ @@@@        DO         J=0 , ;    TK
)@@G@@@A@@@@        LMA,RH     XV,STACK-I,XF.   @^@@@@        DO         J , ;TL
)@@G@@@^@@@@        LMA,U      XV,I.@]@@@@        END @^@@@@. STORE VALUE REGITM
)@@G@@STER  @]@@@@STORE*  PROC@ @@@@        DO         STORE=0 , ;@A@@@@      TN
)@@G@@  SA         XV,STACK,*XT.    @ @@@@        DO         STORE>0 , ;@B@@@@TO
)@@G@@        SA         XV,STACK-STORE(1,1),XF.@]@@@@        END @^@@@@. MOVETP
)@@G@@ VALUES TO STACK  @]@@@@MOVE*   PROC@]@@@@XX*     PROC@ @@@@        LOADTQ
)@@G@@       MOVE(1,I)  @#@@@@        STORE     @]@@@@        END @A@@@@I     TR
)@@G@@  DO         MOVE(1) , XX.    @]@@@@        END @#@@@@. ENTER FUNCTION  TS
)@@G@@@]@@@@CALL*   PROC@ @@@@        LMJ        XL,ENTRY.  @]@@@@        END TT
)@@G@@@#@@@@. ENTER ROUTINE   @]@@@@CALLR*  PROC@ @@@@        LMJ        XL,ENTU
)@@G@@TRYR. @]@@@@        END @#@@@@. LEAVE FUNCTION  @]@@@@RETURN* PROC@^@@@@TV
)@@G@@        J          EXIT.@]@@@@        END @]@@@@. MARK STACK@]@@@@MARK* TW
)@@G@@  PROC@A@@@@        SX         XT,CSTAK,*XC.    @]@@@@        END @ @@@@TX
)@@G@@ . PREPARE TO APPLY FUNCTION  @]@@@@LETS*   PROC@]@@@@        MARK@A@@@@TY
)@@G@@        L,U        R3,LETS(1,1).    @A@@@@        S          R3,STACK,*XTZ
)@@G@@T.    @]@@@@        END @#@@@@. GET NODE TYPE   @]@@@@GETYPE* PROC@ @@@@UA
)@@G@@        AND,U      XV,PAGMSK. @A@@@@        SSL        XV+1,PAGBIT.     UB
)@@G@@@A@@@@        LA,S3      XV+1,PAGTAB,XV+1.@]@@@@        END @#@@@@. GET UC
)@@G@@CAR OR CDR  @]@@@@UPLOW   PROC@^@@@@UPPER*  NAME       4    @^@@@@LOWER*UD
)@@G@@  NAME       3    @C@@@@        LMA        UPLOW(1,1),0,XV,UPLOW(0,0).  UE
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @^@@@@. FOLLOW CAR-CDR CHAIN  @]@@@@CHAIN*  PROC@A@@@@UF
)@@G@@I       DO         CHAIN(1) , ;     @B@@@@        LMA        XV,0,XV,CHAUG
)@@G@@IN(1,I).    @]@@@@        END @^@@@@. BUILD NODE IN MEMORY  @]@@@@NODE* UH
)@@G@@  PROC@B@@@@        LMJ        XL,STORIT(NODE(1,1)).  @]@@@@        END UI
)@@G@@@ @@@@. PUT MESSAGE IN PRINT LINE   @]@@@@EDIT    PROC@^@@@@EDIT*   NAMEUJ
)@@G@@       1    @^@@@@EDITA*  NAME       0    @B@@@@        LMJ        XR,EDUK
)@@G@@CHAR-EDIT(0,0).   @B@@@@I       DO         EDIT(1) , +(EDIT(1,I)).@]@@@@UL
)@@G@@        END @#@@@@. POP TOP OF STACK@]@@@@POP*    PROC@ @@@@        LXM,UM
)@@G@@U      XT,1,XT.   @]@@@@        END @C@@@@/. SET UP ATOMIC SYMBOL TO BE UN
)@@G@@LOADED WITH SYSTEM@]@@@@AT      PROC@]@@@@ATOM*   NAME@ @@@@AF      FORMUO
)@@G@@       18,12,6.   @E@@@@HT*     FUNC       .                   COMPUTE HUP
)@@G@@ASH TOTAL   @^@@@@X(1)    EQU        0.   @ @@@@I       DO         AT(2)UQ
)@@G@@ ,;   @^@@@@J       DO         6 ,; @D@@@@X(1)    EQU        X(1)+(AT(2,UR
)@@G@@I)*/(6*J-36)**077).     @^@@@@        END        X(1).@[@@@@$(2)  @B@@@@US
)@@G@@*       AF         AT(1,1),HT(0),AT(2).   @ @@@@        +          $(10)UT
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@$(10) @B@@@@I       DO         AT(2) , + AT(2,I).     @ @@@@UU
)@@G@@        DO         1 , END    @]@@@@CHARAT* NAME@ @@@@AF      FORM      UV
)@@G@@ 18,12,6.   @ @@@@X(1)    EQU        AT(1,1).   @]@@@@LOOP    NAME@ @@@@UW
)@@G@@$(2)    AF         0,X(1),1.  @ @@@@        +          $(10).     @ @@@@UX
)@@G@@$(10)   +          X(1)*/30   @ @@@@X(1)    EQU        X(1)+1.    @B@@@@UY
)@@G@@        DO         X(1)>AT(2,1) , END     @^@@@@        GO         LOOP UZ
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @ @@@@/. PARAMETERS TO DEFINE SYSTEM@#@@@@. STACK SIZEVA
)@@G@@S     @E@@@@STAKL   EQU        2048.               LENGTH OF VALUE STACKVB
)@@G@@@F@@@@CSTKL   EQU        1024.               LENGTH OF CONTROL STACK    VC
)@@G@@@[@@@@$(10) @D@@@@CSTK    RES        CSTKL+512.          CONTROL STACK  VD
)@@G@@@ @@@@CSTAK   EQU        040000     @[@@@@$(0)  @D@@@@STK     RES       VE
)@@G@@ STAKL.              VALUE STACK    @ @@@@STACK   EQU        040000.    VF
)@@G@@@^@@@@ . SETUP PAGE PARAMETERS@G@@@@PAGBIT  EQU        7.               VG
)@@G@@   PAGES ARE 128 WORDS LONG TODAY   @ @@@@PAGSIZ  EQU        1*/PAGBIT  VH
)@@G@@@C@@@@PAGMSK  EQU        (0377777*/-PAGBIT)*/PAGBIT   @A@@@@PAGNUM  EQU VI
)@@G@@       1*/(17-PAGBIT)   @^@@@@PAGLIS(2)          EQU 0@^@@@@PAGLIS(1)   VJ
)@@G@@       EQU 0@ @@@@. PROCEDURE TO GENERATE PAGES @]@@@@PAGES*  PROC@ @@@@VK
)@@G@@X       EQU        PAGES(1,2) @ @@@@XXX(1)  EQU        PAGES(1,1) @[@@@@VL
)@@G@@$(X)  @]@@@@LOOP    NAME@ @@@@        +          PAGLIS(X)  @C@@@@      VM
)@@G@@  DO         XXX(2) ,PAGLIS*(X) EQU $-1   @ @@@@        RES        PAGSIVN
)@@G@@Z-1   @ @@@@XXX(1)  EQU        XXX(1)-1   @B@@@@        DO         XXX(1VO
)@@G@@)>0 , GO LOOP     @^@@@@XXX(2)  EQU        1    @]@@@@        END @D@@@@VP
)@@G@@. PROCEDURE NECESSARY AT END TO FINISH THINGS OFF     @]@@@@WINDUP* PROCVQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@$(7)  @B@@@@ENDCHK* .          END I-BANK CHECKSUM    @[@@@@$(6)  VR
)@@G@@@F@@@@AVAIL*  +          PAGLIS(2).          D-BANK AVAILABLE PAGE LIST VS
)@@G@@@F@@@@        +          PAGLIS(1)           I-BANK    ''      ''   ''  VT
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @D@@@@/. GENERATE AVAILABLE SPACE & ATOMS LOADED WITH VU

)@@G@@T 'LEFTSH','IFT@@@'     @A@@@@        ATOM       TERPRI 'TERPRI'  @A@@@@XD

)@@G@@,'SS@@@@'.  @C@@@@        ATOM       EXPLODE 'EXPLOD','E@@@@@'.   @C@@@@YN

)@@G@@@C@@@@        ATOM       PLENGTH-2 'PLENGT','H2@@@@'. @A@@@@        ATOMYQ
